deck_description: My other decks 2022: https://ygoprodeck.com/abc-dragon-buster-deck-2022/ https://ygoprodeck.com/invoked-dogmatika-control-deck-2022/ https://ygoprodeck.com/mysterune-3/ https://ygoprodeck.com/ritual-evolution-2022/ https://ygoprodeck.com/my-very-evil-twins-2022/   About my deck mhhh, basically one point here it is about used hand traps. I use those that I think will be the most universal against most of the decks (not only Meta). Here, of course, a lot depends on the archetype of the opponents monsters and their support cards . Of course, Ash is dominant here. Why then I only use two. I use Effect Veiler to have an additional emergency card to pay the cost Galaxy Soldier. Other cards will also be good here such as Ghost Ogre or Nibiru or other powerful light hand traps. Here, of course, all depends on the opponent's deck. Or maybe more about Pot's. I used 3. They perfectly complement the decks and make it move (together with other engins). The most controversial is Pot of Desires. Someone will say that this is crazy with a deck like this. And I will say: Is it not madness to leave the field blank when you have dead hands ? And if you have a good hand: you add what you have to add, you are using what you are supposed to use, you are doing a combo and finally you use Pot of Desires. Maybe something else can be strengthened hehe GL HF. Here's a video : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n3WH0gtc_lo

Bullet + Stormer //////////////////////////////////////////////// TechnoPlay/Rulings: You can Still use the SS Effect from Hand of Infinitrack Monsters on Set Monsters, as Long as the Monsters are PROPER TYPE and ATTRIBUTE. The Activation and Search effect of Forward is HOPT. Meanwhile the 2nd effect of Forward is SOPT, so you can use multiples same turn. Knuckle + Overdrive = "Machina Overdrive" SS effect from deck will RESOLVE WITHOUT EFFECT if the TARGET LEAVE the FIELD BEFORE RESOLUTION, because Overdrive check names at resolution. So cl1 Overdrive cl2 Knuckle SEND ITSELF don't works. But cl1 Overdrive cl2 Knuckle SEND Box for Example works. Super Dora + Overdrive = cl1 Overdrive cl2 Super Dora tgt itself works because you don't need to destroy the target in order to summon. It will SS the Machina monster but fail destroying Super Dora due to either Dora Quick eff, Goliath's or Dingirsu's Protection. Ice Dragon's Prison/D. D. Crow vs Knuckle/Overdrive = cl1 IDP/D. D. Crow target Bullet Train cl2 Knuckle target itself and Bullet Train = SOLVE WITHOUT EFFECT cl1 IDP/D. D. Crow target Bullet Train cl2 Overdrive target Bullet Train, Banished Tunneller and Banished Trencher = SOLVE WITHOUT EFFECT "Droll&Lock Bird" vs Overdrive = can play around Droll&Lock Bird using Overdrive GY effect during the DRAW Phase. "Machina CITADEL" effect to Destroy will Resolve without effect if the target leave the field before resolution, because Citadel checks ATK stats at resolution. "Machina CITADEL" 1st effect to destroy will ATTEMPT to Destroy Super Dora and Opponent's Monsters: cl1 CITADEL target Super Dora cl2 Super Dora tgt itself = DESTROY all Opponent's Monsters with 32atk or Less but fail Destroying Dora due to either Dora Quick eff, Goliath's or Dingirsu's Protection. "Machina FORTRESS" 2nd effect its MANDATORY so it Will ALWAYS be Chain Link 1, in the case of crash in battle phase Citadel eff in GY will be cl2. As long as a XYZ have battled, either Opponent's or yours, during your turn you can attempt to SS Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder For example you can do: Goliath atk opponent's XYZ in Defense position and in M2 use Stormer eff tribute Goliath and Goliath eff Attach to Stormer and AA-ZEUS on top of Stormer. ///////////////////////////////////////////////Comments: Bullet Train on the field as soon as possible has you playing around Nibiru with at least adding a follow up in the end phase. You activate your worst cards first and best last after bait interactions. For example if you open with Starter and Redeployment you start playing with Starter and save the Redeployment for later. RANK-9 play is more sensitive to hand traps compared to standard deck play. What you can do in turn 3: Use Anchor Drill to summon Box and go to a RANK-8 DINGIRSU and use eff to send a card or Attach 1 Infinitrack banished like Trencher for example and go to battle phase to make AA-ZEUS with 4 materials. Other plays: Discard a card to revive Knuckle to tribute for Dozer and summon Tunneller/Trencher and because you already have Stormer in GY you go to LINK-1 Goliath and use Stormer eff in GY and in the resolution use Goliath eff to attach to Stormer and use eff to Search whatever fix your hand like Citadel/Derricrane/Fortress. And again you can use Tunneller eff Pot of Avarice and make Ballista to add Box and Anchor Drill. ***OTK Version: NS Anchor Drill and eff Special Dozer and eff Special Trencher and LINK-1 Goliath and Stormer play to tribute Goliath and attach Goliath to Stormer to search Citadel Knuckle eff send Citadel and use Anchor Drill level manipulation eff on Dozer to summon RANK-9 Slicer and pop 2 cards: one of your monsters and one card opponent's controls to trigger Citadel in GY and finally use Trencher just to summon anything and make LINK- 1 Goliath for more 1k damage for game. ***This combination of Dozer + Anchor Drill + Box can play after too disruption in any point like in Anchor Drill eff or Dozer eff becauser you have Knuckle and Stormer in GY that can search or send to GY any Earth Machine like Citadel to control the game.

deck_excerpt: Kaijus take opponent's beatsticks away, and Yosenjus get your Kaijus back. Back row traps help for your protection.
deck_description: Pretty simple deck mechanic here. Take away opponent's monsters with Kaijus, and use the Yosenjus to get your Kaiju back (Yosenju 1) or beat over it with an extra deck monster. Yosenjus come back to hand after normal summon, so it's a good idea to have back row protection and interruptions. There are a bunch of different cards to use and it's pretty easy to stay on the cheaper side. I have two droplets hence why there are two in there, but you can easily replace those with anything else. You can also interchange the traps (most people wouldn't play SMF, but I like it for the return). Side deck is also very interchangeable of course for whatever the meta is, and I would even have some back row disruptors possibly in there (Harpie's FD, TT, etc).

deck_excerpt: An almost complete personal deck for winning against NPC's in Legacy of the Duelist: Link Evolution, just about everytime. "FTK" more than 9 times out
deck_description: Add Makyura to your hand with Painful Choice or Pot of Duality (or just draw it), then discard it with Dark World Dealings or Graceful Charity, after that use Painful Choice to thin out the deck (preferably by having another Painful Choice as one of the 5 cards, since the AI seems to always choose Painful Choice when you go with 5 Spell Cards, unless Chicken Game is one of the cards, then the AI seems to choose that instead.)  Also keep a Magical Mallet in hand at all times if you can, so that you can shuffle the Exodia pieces you've likely aquired back into the deck (in case you end up with something that might have you discard an Exodia piece) and draw new cards to likely extend the play unless you get really unlucky. (I am currently testing to swap out one Magical Mallet for a Dark Factory of Mass Production, to render this less of a problem, or to not completely screw you over if the opponent carries an annoying hand trap in their starting hand or something.)  Notes:  I'm not completely sure running 3x Dark World Dealings is the best idea with the discard effect. (Though it is more of a niche "This could go wrong in very specific situations" thing and it does help with discarding Makyura the Destructor now that I'm using a RML instead of Armageddon Knight.)  I switched out the Armageddon Knight for Royal Magical Library, as I already have plenty of ways to get Makyura to the graveyard, and RML helps extend plays those few times the "Heart of the cards" is not with me, heh.  Im wondering which out of Foolish Burial and Reinforcement of the Army would actually be the most consistent and complimentary. (Probably Foolish Burial considering I went for a RML instead of an Armageddon Knight.)  Also, I'm trying to minimize the amount of Trap cards, while still not rendering Makyuras effect completely moot, and Reckless Greed in this case works really well with Graceful Charity when activated from the hand as a chain, as you'll draw two extra cards before having to discard, which also makes it less likely to have things go kaputt.

deck_excerpt: Brave Token Eldlich

The Yu-Gi-Oh! Trading Card Game

Known as the Yu-Gi-Oh! Official Card Game (遊☆戯☆王オフィシャルカードゲーム, Yū-Gi-Ō Ofisharu Kādo Gēmu) in Asia, is a Japanese collectible card game developed and published by Konami. deck_excerpt: finally an Orcust Deck that does not lose to handtraps on it's normal summon
deck_description:
I've been using Orcust for 2 years and keep losing to handtraps on my normal summon. so i build this deck with the mindset that my opponent will always ash or imperm the trigger effect of Scrap Recycler or Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight. Yes, you need to draw specifically a starter and an extender, but at least you'll still be able to play through those handtraps with these extender. I'm also using some Sky Striker card as a pseudo called by the grave to dodges handtraps on the activation of Scrap Wyvern or 'Rusty Bardiche'. So the way you do these line is for example: (Scenario)
  1. you summon Scrap Recycler and activates it's effect to send a machine monster from your deck to the GY, and let say your opponent ash/imperm your 'Scrap Recycler'. so then you activate Cyberdark Claw searching Cyberdark Realm which then search your additional normal summon Cyberdark Chimera. Then with these 2 you make Scrap Wyvern. With the 'Cyberdark' cards, you will an extender and also a free pop with Scrap Wyvern's effect saving you an important card that normally you got to destroy or if you want to preserve your Scrap Wyvern. and then from there you just go ahead and do the full combo and pray to lord jesus god Cimoooooooo that your opponent doesn't have anymore interaction
  2. somehow you draw your World Wand/your Machina Citadel alongside Scrap Recycler. These are not considered to be a brick, cuz with Scrap Recycler you will then send your Machina Fortress, which then you can summon by sending either the World Wand/Machina Citadel. and with Machina Citadel in grave, your Scrap Wyvern are basically immune to Ash Blossom cuz you can chainblock it's effect.
  3. The Girsu line are basically the same as the scrap line, if you draw an extender with girsu, you won't be able to end on an Apoloussa, but you'll at least end on Rusty Bardiche + I:P + 2 Fog Blade + Ding in grave. so it is potentially 5 interruption which is not bad.
Keep in mind, that this build of the deck are not perfect and can still be improved. i just really really hate losing to handtrap that much. oh also, this deck hard loses to spells and traps that interact with your board (example: Lightning Storm and Evenly Match) cuz the end board only deals with monster effect with no spell/trap negation.

deck_excerpt: Probably the closest thing to a competitive Starry Night deck as of right now. Fun to play in a casual setting.
deck_description:
I. Deck Pros and Cons Pros
  • Slightly more versatile with use of the extra deck
  • Very high search power
  • Can lock the board down when going first
Cons
  • Fragile fragile fragile
  • Will almost never pull off any OTKs
  • Struggles going second
  • Needs setup for most card negation and destruction
  • Continuous spell and trap reliant, weak to backrow removal
II. Going Second If you have the choice of going first, always go first because of the amount of traps and setup you need. If you think you'll be going second after a round, you could remove cards such as Summon Limit , Honest , and Barrier Statue of the Heavens . Dark Ruler No More and Evenly Matched help you be able to be able to search and destroy comfortably without being interrupted. Artifact Lancea is also a good card to side in as it can be used by Starry Night Ceremony to search for your dragon. Other options for the side deck include Nibiru, the Primal Being , Artifact Scythe , and Artifact Sanctum .

deck_description: The only really good combo in this deck requires crimson resonator and serziel, watcher of the evil eye, so a lot of the deck is just cards to search them and extenders. The deck really lacked consistency and I had to add couple of pot of desires even though I like using the extra deck as a toolbox and I feel like the pot banishes too much of it. The deck just really wasn't consistent when I tested it without the pots. But I feel like the deck maintains more cards in hand than my edge imp variant of the deck, but edge imp engine is maybe a better at recovery due to edge imp scissor. The biggest problem of the deck is probably that it is very weak to disruption. So going second is usually hard against combo and control decks, and going first requires the use use of crossout designators and caleld by the grave. The other problem is that the recovery is quite weak for non-tuner monsters. Red rising dragon can revive tuners etc but you really have to get another serziel to your hand or chaos ruler the chaotic magical dragon to your graveyard to recover from board wipes. Often this is not needed however since the goal is to just go into a mean disruption board. Overall I really like how this turned out. It is fairly consistent and red super nova dragon is just a boss. https://youtu.be/w1nHL-Ey6Gw

deck_excerpt: A pretty fun Fusion Summoning centered strategy.
deck_description: Hi, I'm Grayewick. I mostly play Fusion decks and I've decided to share my Branded Albaz deck list. I've been play testing and building this deck since it first got released in Dawn of Majesty, from splashing it with Darklords to making it work with Valkyries with Condemned Witch, and I think this is by far the best iteration of the deck that I've been building. A few questions you might have: • "Why run Despian Comedy?" - I'm actually surprised as to why not a lot of people run this card, considering the fact that it helps you dodge targeting effects like Infinite Impermanence and Effect Veiler. • "Why run 3 Branded Condemnation unlike most lists?" - It's a searchable Solemn Warning that also helps you recur your "Branded" Spells/Traps from your GY, which are either Screams of the Branded or Branded Exile as your main targets. A recyclable and searchable Super Polymerization is always great for a Fusion deck. • "4 Destiny HERO monsters and a Dark Magician?" - Unlike most Fusion decks that run DPE/Dragoon, these five monsters aren't really bricks, since all of them are DARK monsters, and there are hands that you'd be glad that you've drawn at least 1 Destiny HERO monster and/or Dark Magician, since there are combo lines that allows you to bring out both two of either Dragoon, DPE, and/or a Dynatag boosted Dystopia. • "No Prosperity/Handtraps/Crossout?" - Maybe it's just me, but I don't think running Prosperity in a deck with an already tight enough Extra Deck space is a good idea. If you feel like doing it, sure. It just isn't my cup of tea. If you wanna run hand traps, I suggest only those with LIGHT/DARK Attributes, for obvious reasons but then, you'd much rather run Kaijus of said Attributes/Santa Claws and cards that immediately address threats than trying to generate card advantage (which this deck already doesn't have much problem doing anyway).  Strengths: • It's a bit toolbox-y (as per most Fusion decks nowadays), but variety and flexibility is always a welcome trait especially for Fusion decks. • It breaks monster heavy boards with ease, and with the addition of Abyssal Dragon Alba Renatus, breaking an entire Dragon Link board has never been easier. • Much like other meta Fusion decks in the past, it can grind just as hard as them. It's a resource focused deck, and even with the help of Lubellion, the Searing Dragon, you'd still wanna be cautious. • Can easily play around Droll & Lock bird and most hand traps, and despite being able to swarm easily, getting hit by a Nibiru isn't really as punishing. Weaknesses: • Does not have an innate answer to back row, although that's what your side deck is for. • It does brick at certain occasions, though it can easily be remedied by having at least 1 LIGHT/DARK monster in either field, usually. • Mirror matches can be REALLY tough and grindy so as per usual, be mindful of your resources. • Floodgates, as per usual. Some other neat Fusion monster/Fusion engine choices for your choosing: • You can never go wrong with Invoked in any Fusion strategy. • A Buster Blader engine with ratios of your liking. Prologue of the Destruction Swordsman is a crazy card. • If you're not a fan of Despian Comedy, you could always substitute it with either a The Light - Hex-Sealed Fusion or Qadshaddoll Keios for El Shaddoll Winda. • Dark Cavalry or Dark Paladin aren't bad ideas either, considering that you have four Warrior-type monsters (five, if you're also using a Buster Blader engine.) Both are additional negations and are decent beat sticks, one of which pierces. • More semi-generic Super Polymerization targets like Despian Quaeritis, Despian Proskenion, Mysterion the Dragon Crown, etc.   Closing thoughts: Invoked Dogmatika and Dragon Link/Dragonmaid are the most fun match ups you can have, and "Konami pls ban Verte" KEKW

deck_excerpt: Brutal Dinosaur Archetype.
deck_description:
Keep Halfing your LP to 1. Negate. Disrupt. Stun. Beat Down. 
  • There is no needing of Conventional Dinosaur Engine.
  • Rexturm is the Boss: One Side Skill Drain. With Deadly Bites in Battles. Turning all Opponent's monster into simps. Damage Step Player. Beating Over every other Boss monsters in the meta game atm. You name it. Dragoon, DPE, Everthing...
  • Kentregina and Therizia are the Waifu Bosses and Searcher.
  • Diplos is helpful: a mill and 500 burn ftw. Will there be another main deck monster? We'll be waiting. Meanwhile. Enjoy the boy.
  • Ferret Flame is Madly Strong with these guys.
  • Lord of the Heavenly Prison is a searcher, protector, defender, Beater. Be careful for what you search for. Use it wisely. Next turn. Only.
  • Gravedigger Trap Hole is a tech card for my own favor, over Trap Trick and Torrential Tribute. As you can see, it deals with Hand trap monsters, and ones that activates in Grave, or Banish Zones.
  • Dinorphia Reversion: some says it's a bit harder to set it up, but i found it's not the case since you can always have A Fusion Boss on the field. Copying Solemn Powerful Negation, and Sonic. You can trade it for the 3rd Solemn Strike or Sonic if you want, Stealthbegia would make it Free to play anyway.
  • Stealthbegia can make some excellent play like burning Eldlich then chain Called by the Grave, free 2500lp.
  • Too bad I can't put Dinorphia Shell into the deck. If only the token could be used For Brute and  be Fusion Materials. But it can't. What a pity.
  • Imperial Order: the deck doesn't sweat paying LP.
Pay Attention to these Threats:
  • Super Polymerization ( no counter, can only play around it with Rivalry of Warlord,  Imperial Order...), be more careful dueling with Despia Albaz, Predaplant, Heroes...
  • E Hero Honest Neo: don't wait til Dam step, just Brute the attacker away.
  • Some burning Effect: That despia fusion dragon, Kill it asap, and remember to activate eff of the normal Traps in grave when seeing A burning coming ( Sworld Soul, Trickstar... )
  • Sky Striker Hayate: Brute it, Ferret Flame it, Solemn it, don't let it attack
  Timing to flip cards and activate effects can only be improved by playing more games and becoming skillful with the deck.    I have been playing with this Archetype for a long while, Since its first appearance. With Frenzy and Rexturm come out recently, the deck has got so much stronger. Most Interesting Matchup for me until now are Sky Striker and Eldlich. Thrilling games. Losing dramatically to Sky Striker once and never again since then. Had some easy win also. Beating Eldlich almost everytime, and that one time a kid got so angry he started to use mean words instead of accepting a losing game, not realizing that if getting beaten with opponent at 16lp is a humiliation, it's for him not for me. Hey Yuto on DuelingNexus, Grow up.

deck_excerpt: The second iteration of my previous Branded Albaz deck.
deck_description: Hi, it's me again, Grayewick the Fusion strategy enjoyer, back with my favorite Fusion archetype so far aside from Invoked and Shaddolls, Branded Albaz. This time splashing the Buster Blader package in a 60-card deck, pretty hefty but surprisingly consistent. My previous Branded Albaz deck list already have more than enough Dragon hate, it won't hurt for us to add even more. Not much significant change(s) in terms of the Branded Albaz ratios, only in the Extra Deck where I've decided to cut some more generic Fusion monsters to test other possible options (I am actually heavily considering Mysterion the Dragon Crown just because there are a lot of lines that allows you to make it with ease). Also, one thing I forgot mentioning in my previous deck list is that Magicians' Souls speeds up the deck significantly, not only because it draws you cards (which actually works well by discarding your Branded Condemnation or Branded Opening) but it also sends Dark Magician from the deck to the GY. You could always cut Destiny HERO - Dynatag and other Destiny HERO monster to make some space for it. Keeping it short and simple: Branded Fusion, Magicians' Souls, and Buster Whelp of the Destruction Swordsman is a guaranteed Buster Blader, the Dragon Destroyer Swordsman with Buster lock during your opponent's turn, either Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon (recommended if you opened Incredible Ecclesia, the Virtuous) or Destiny HERO - Destroyer Phoenix Enforcer, and an additional 2 interruptions in the form of Branded Exile, mainly depending on your discards, which are made even better with drawing the "bricks" (Dark Magician, the Destiny HERO monsters, etc.) Side deck is always debatable, but I still do highly suggest Kaijus and outs that immediately address the board (Lightning Storm, Evenly Matched, etc.) than hand traps and floodgates. Note: I really tried making it as compact as possible, but 47-50 cards is the lowest I could get it to work without sacrificing consistency and options.

deck_excerpt: No "Destiny HERO" Engine
deck_description:
The goal of this deck is to get Ultimate Conductor Tyranno out as fast as possible, while using other monsters in the deck's toolbox to protect it and negate any possible plays by the opponent. Use the "Scrap" monsters to get Synchro monsters. Take advantage of the "Giant Rex" floating effect, allowing for quick rank 4 plays. This is an alternative version of the Dinosaur deck that does not include the "Destiny HERO" engine, for those who do not want to use it. If cost is a constraint, one can use the PSY-Frame engine to replace some other hand traps in the deck (Note that a level 3 tuner must be run at all times if you opt-out of Ash). The most potent combo in this deck involves either a Turn 1 play with "Lost World", or Turn 2 play with only "Scrap Raptor".
  • Activate "Lost World"
  • Summon "Scrap Raptor" and destroy him using his own effect, adding "Scrap Chimera" to the hand
  • Normal Summon "Scrap Chimera" and use its effect to summon "Scrap Raptor" from the GY
  • Link into "Scrap Wyvern", use his effect to Special Summon "Scrap Raptor", then destroy "Scrap Raptor" and the "Jurraegg Token" using that same effect.
  • Use the effect of "Lost World" to destroy a Baby Dinosaur or Overtex Qoatlus in the deck instead. Use their effects accordingly.
  • Use the other effect "Scrap Wyvern" to special Summon "Scrap Golem" from the deck.
  • Use "Scrap Golem" to Special Summon "Scrap Raptor" from the GY
  • Link into "Crystron Halqifibrax" and Special Summon "Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring"
  • Synchro Summon "Borreload Savage Dragon" and equip "Scrap Wyvern" to it from the GY

deck_excerpt: Dragon grave recursion / fusion monster deck.
deck_description: Odd-Eyes Revolution Dragon, Back to the Front, Monster Reborn, Odd-Eyes Advance Dragon, Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon are all here to play cards from graveyards, and Odd-Eyes Advance Dragon and Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon can also hit things.  Albion the Shrouded, Fallen of Albaz, and the "Branded" set of cards allow us to play that archetype, as well as providing most of our fusion monsters and fusion support.  Dogmatika Punishment is great for both destroying things, and putting reanimation targets into the grave.  Dragon Ravine is great for grave filler, and Waking the Dragon's just for fun as much as anything else.  The Dark -- Hex-Sealed Fusion is also great for fusions.  Galactic Spiral Dragon and Nebula Dragon are both decent fillers, while Keeper of the Shrine is there just in case I ever actually have to properly tribute summon something.  Into the extra deck we have: the Branded friends, Albion, Brigrand, and Titaniklad, which work with Fallen of Albaz, have some not-bad abilities, and are beefy enough reanimation targets.  Starving Venom Fusion Dragon is an alternate for the three above, as Dark's a pretty common attribute at my table, and he's not bad either, despite easy requirements.  Starving Venemy Dragon's a pet card, but it's also decent, and weakens opponents over time if they can't get rid of it and/or have a grave-combo-heavy deck.  Beelze and Beelzeus are strictly grave fodder/reanimation targets. Wouldn't be too hard to build into, I just don't care to. Once they're out they're hard to get rid of anyways.

deck_excerpt: Use dinosaurs to either search out Ultimate Conductor Tyranno and summon it with its effect or use double evolution pill to special summon it from the
deck_description: Use dinosaurs to either search out Ultimate Conductor Tyranno and summon it with its effect or use Double Evolution Pill to special summon it from the deck!  The dinosaur archetype got a new card in the ocg called Uradora of Fate. What that card does is: Pay 1000 lp to target 1 of your monsters and it (until the end of your opponents next turn) gains 1000 attack and when it destroys a monster by battle, reveal the bottom card of your deck to put either on top or on the bottom of your deck, if the card was a dinosaur, dragon, sea serpent, or wyrm monster, draw 1 card and gain 1000 lp for every 1000 attack the card has.  The reason that this card is so broken, is that Ultimate Conductor Tyranno can attack multiple times per turn and can beat over almost anything that it attacks so it will activate the effect multiple times to potentially draw a ton of cards and gain a ton of lp.

deck_excerpt: A fun, Ritual good stuff deck.
deck_description: Hi, it's me again, Grayewick the Fusion strategy enjoyer, back with something different. This time, it's Impcantation Dogmatika, with Blue-Eyes Chaos MAX Dragon as its main boss monster (despite having 4 others). I've been having a lot of fun with this deck for a while so I decided to share it with y'all. A few questions you might have: • "What's with the messed up Extra Deck?" - for none other than Ghost Reaper & Winter Cherries, of course! The only thing you'll gonna be using here are the two Elder Entity N'tss, Psy-Framelord Omega, the three Shaddoll Fusion monsters, and Nephthys, the Sacred Flame. Sure, floodgating your opponent with El Shaddoll Winda is nice and all, but there's nothing more fun than having your opponent stare at five gigantic Ritual Monsters under There Can Be Only One and Skill Drain. • "Nadir Servant at the Side?" - Yeah, it kinda gets redundant with Preparation of Rites, BUT, you can always fix that post siding. Strengths: • It's a pretty straightforward deck. All you gotta do is summon a big Ritual monster you wanna use then boost it with White Exalted of Dogmatika upon her Ritual Summon (just make sure you target the correct ones). • A lot of monsters with innate protection, like Blue-Eyes Chaos MAX Dragon,  Drytron Meteonis Draconids, and Archfiend's Awakening and interruptions in the form of Cyber Angel Vrash, Nekroz of Trishula, and Megalith Bethor. •  It isn't reliant to the Extra Deck to make plays. • It's fun to play! Weaknesses: • It can brick. (Unsurprisingly) • No innate back row removal, except for Nekroz of Trishula's effect. More tech options: • Pot of Prosperity/Pot of Extravagance for draw power • You can substitute some of your beat sticks with more control/stun oriented Ritual monsters like Amorphactor Pain, the Imagination Dracoverlord and Magician of Black Chaos MAX, or an additional removal with Cerulean Sacred Phoenix of Nephthys. Just be careful with the potential type overlaps for the purposes of There Can Be Only One.

Activate it twice so you get 2 lvl 5 materials for your Pleiades. With Caduceus you can get Star chart an draw 1.  4- Galaxy soldier + discard material = easy CDI  Use Siat and Sombre for recovery/play-starts and that's pretty much it. Twinkle can be used very easely with 1 constellar in GY to make Pleiades, so dont be shy to search it with the Pollux+Sheratan combo. deck_excerpt: Almost pure @Ignister deck whose goal is to bring out Arrival with at least 5000 ATK
deck_description: The goal is to bring out Arrival with ideally at least 5000 ATK; it is unaffected by other cards' effects, which would most probably win you the game unless they have cards like Kaiju that could take it off the field through atypical means. There are many routes to the boss monster; however, the most practical sequence is Dark Infant (search out Ignister AILand) >> Cyberse Wicckid (search out Bururu) >> Splash Mage (don't use effect for the meantime) >> Transcode Talker (summon Splash Mage then use its effect) >> Dark Templar (optional, depending on availability of elements required) >> Arrival (with ideally at least 5000 ATK). Of course, other cards (@Ignister effect monsters, resurrection spells, searching spells) are omitted in the sequence due to the indeterminate game state. The logic behind the sequence is that the field spell Ignister AILand only allows you to special summon when there are no monsters on your Main Monster zone. These link monsters serve as buffers, which allow you to special summon @Ignister effect monsters from your hand or through spells (FAIghting Spirit, AIdle Reborn). You have to keep track which @Ignister monsters have activated their effects due to the once per turn restriction. Also, you must keep track of the elements of your summoned monsters in order to fulfill the requirements for Arrival. If you have Transcode Talker (Earth), Splash Mage (Water), and another monster summoned by Splash Mage's effect while you have Doshin (Earth) and/or Hiyari (Water) on your hand, you can go for Dark Templar (Dark) and use its effect along with resurrection spells (FAIghting Spirit, AIdle Reborn) or a search spell (AI Meet You) in order to bring out 5 different elements from the GY or hand. For emergencies, use Link Disciple (Light) to replace a redundant element. When Link summoning, don't forget to start from the effect monsters all the way to the Link monsters in ascending Link rating; starting from the Link-3 Transcode Talker or Dark Templar will only allow you to select at most three other materials since Arrival is a Link-6 (This is for Dueling Nexus mechanics). If you feel like you can't bring out 5000 ATK Arrival due to the lack of resources, you can choose to go for other @Ignister monsters (Fire Phoenix, Light Dragon, etc.) or Accesscode Talker for board cleaning. If there are other useful cards that were not included here, please leave a comment so that I can broaden my horizons through the spirit of learning, and perhaps grief my opponents with a stronger deck. Thank you for viewing.

deck_excerpt: A low rarity deck I used to farm in Master Duel with a simple and straightforward game plan.
deck_description: Hi, it's me again, Grayewick the Fusion strategy enjoyer, back with another deck that isn't a Fusion deck again, strangely enough but I digress. This is the deck that I've used to grind in Master Duel, Tenyi ft. Vanity's Fiend, Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax, & Archnemeses Protos. It's absolutely cheap, you only really need two in-archetype UR cards and 3 in-archetype SR cards, and the entire Tenyi core in the main deck is literally made up of Rares and Commons. This deck has only one goal in mind, and that is to set up Avramax as soon as you can and summon either Vanity's Fiend going 1st or Archnemeses Protos as soon as you can. A few questions you might have: • "Why Vanity's Fiend instead of Vanity's Ruler?" - Because the former only requires you to tribute one monster for its Tribute Summon, and that actually matters because it allows you to have enough monsters for a Synchro Summon of a defensive monster like Adamancipator Risen - Dragite alongside your Avramax, which is actually a better option than Borreload Savage Dragon since Shaman of the Tenyi prevents you from activating the effects of non-"Tenyi" monsters that are Special Summoned from the Extra Deck upon using its effect to Special Summon a Wyrm monster from the GY (most likely a Mare Mare). • "Evenly Matched and Ice Dragon's Prison on the main?" - Yes, there are no side decks (as of now) in Master Duel. These slots could be for any high impact/consistency staples, really, and that includes your hand traps if you're the type of guy who prefers Maxx "C" over anything. If you don't have any defensive hand traps yet, you can add more Mare Mare, Shthana, and Mapura in a ratio of your liking. I wanna keep it short and sweet since it's a pretty straightforward deck to play, and there's really nothing much else to say about it. Have fun.

deck_description: Hello boy and girls, today is the day!! An awesome day, a very good day indeed. Sky Striker are rockting in the new and most anticipated MASTER DUEL,So this an all time favorite list that I had the pleasure to build, and everything for free. Do you wanna see?   Disclaimers      This game follows an aumagnation of banlist (OCG + TCG), so a lot( and I Say really a lot) are different from the usual cards that you are familiar with. So expect cards like MAX “C” and other abomination.   Starters 3x Sky Striker Ace - Raye: This cute girl or your main starter. She can bring almost every   sky striker monster in your extra deck and makes a good protection for your Links sky striker monsters against destruction, 'cause Raye can bring herself from the GY and link again in another sky striker.    2x Sky Striker Ace - Roze : The fearsome antagonist of Raye,  Roze can be another great starter for the sky striker link play. The effect that she can be summoned with another sky striker is good, but the effect that she returns to the field when an opponent's monster is removed from the extra monster zone is beyond insane, additionally can also negate the effect of another opponent's monster. This card is insane.    1x Sky Striker Mecha - Hornet Drones:  another way to summon the links monster. Furthermore it can be used for other combos utilizing link-2 monsters like  Sky Striker Ace - Zeke.    1x Reinforcement of the army : search Raye of Roze depending on your needs.   2x Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage! : Guess who is at 2? Sky F@#$ing striker Moblize engage! This card is a pot of greed on legs, searching for sky striker cards and with the right set up, makes 1+ in card advantage by drawing another card from the deck. The cherry in the cake is that it is not once per turn, so you can recycle with Striker Ace - Kagari. This card was banned for a reason and I’m happy to see its back.   1x Chicken Game:  Man.. I love this card , it is so risky yet so  satisfying to use to draw 3 or 4 cards,  almost a prosperity. I wish I could play it on tcg.   Pseudo Starters   They’re considered starter only if certain conditions are fulfilled (combination with other specific cards, luck in a draw, etc.)   1x Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero + 2x Sky Striker Mecha Modules - Multirole:  Area zero can dig more in your deck while finding a copy of the sky striker monster or a sky striker spell. In other cases, you can use  Multirole to pop Area zero and get a free summon of Roze or Raye.   Extenders   1x Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero:  You can search some cards by dig 3 card in your deck, but you have to pop one of  your cards. You can use this effect  like explained above  or  to pop any monster of your opponent  in combination with  Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor.   1x Terraforming:  Search  Sky Striker Airspace - Area Zero to help in your plays, additionally you can search Chicken Game .   1x Upstart Goblin:  Draw a card, nothing to explain.   2x Sky Striker Mecha Modules - Multirole: This card shines with your second effect to use every Sky Striker spell … all over again. Insane and deserve to be limited. Also, make any sky striker magic cards irresponsible by any effect of your opponent. This card, at least for me, worked  better at 2 instead of 3. Maybe in the future I’ll cut to 1.   3x Sky Striker Ace - Hayate: She is amazing and  the perfect monster to stall your opponent with Mystic mine if you decide to side it. She can also send a sky striker spell to late recovery with Sky Striker Ace - Kagari.   3x Sky Striker Ace - Kagari: The effect of adding to your hand any sky striker spell is outrageous. Cycle spell, recover spell that was negated, search cards in conjunction with Sky Striker Ace - Hayate… this card does so much for one card that deserves the time that was limited. Now you can even recycle Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage!... what a time to be alive.   3x Sky Striker Ace - Shizuku: This is your primally way to get the spell  like Sky Striker Mobilize - Engage! And every thing that you wanted, too bad it only in you final phase, but She can be a fine protection by lowering the opponent's monster attack by 100 for each spell card in the GY.         Controller/Defenders   2x Infinite Impermanence + 2 x effect Veiler : Handtraps are always welcome to control any kind of play ( or plan) that your opponent may have. Additionally Infinite impermanence  can be set.   3x Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring+ 3x MAX “C”: your primaries hand trap to stop your opponent from playing., ash to be herself, annoying as a spoiled brat. Max”C” in other hand is the most annoying insect that may have existed on the face of earth. Man what broken card, thank God this is not o Tcg,. May rest in peace Combo deck.    2x There Can Be Only One: Decks based on one type card (Salamagreat or dragon link  for example) suffers a lot with this majestic stall card.   2x Sky Striker Mecha - Widow Anchor: one of the most broken cards in this archetype, that spell can steal a monster in the opponent’s field to use for attack, link folder or furthermore can negate an effect of a monster if you wish, becoming one of the most versatile cards in your deck. I’ll miss the second one   3x Sky Striker Mecha - Shark Cannon: Your D .D . Crow in spell form, can distrusted some plays of your opponent, and also can special summon one of this opponent's monsters  in your side of the field to generate advantage (Masked HERO Dark Law For example) or to be a  link folder.   1x Sky Striker Ace - Zeke + 1x Sky Striker Ace - Kaina: Both have a similar role that can be exploited in the opponent’s turn. Zeke on the other hand, can be used with Roze and Raye to banish a monster in your summon.   2x Mind Control:  Communism in the form of a card. Is our monster now. deck_excerpt: This deck is focused around accessible UR cards and SR cards. Salamangreats offer easy Link plays, easy GY recovery and search tools. You can board wi
deck_description: Your main strategy is to start with Foxy (for +1), Link summon Balelynx (Link 1) and grab Sanctuary (for +1 and protection),  and/or use special summon bodies like Jack Jaguar and Spinny to advance to Sunlight Wolf (Link 2) and special summon another body to his link (for +1), then advance into Heatleo (Link 3) for non-destruction Spell/Trap removal or Pyro Phoenix (Link 4) and activate Sanctuary to summon him on top of itself to full wipe your opponent's board.  After you finish your Link plays you should end up with at least 1 Balelynx and a few Salamangreats in your GY. After this point you can set your counters (Roar, Solemn Judgment and Infinite Impermanence) and prepare yourself for the coming turn. Roar is basically a budget Solemn Judgment that has no cost and only requires you to have 1 Salamangreat Link monster (which you can always have, even Balelynx works) and you can recover it afterwards when you Link summon on top of the same monster with Sanctuary's effect. Make sure you start your plays with Foxy to benefit from pure +1 and use your Circle to pick whatever Salamangreat you are currently missing in your hand. More names = more summons, because each Salamangreat effect monster has a hard once per turn tied to its special summon.  Salamangreats are very versatile and offer easy recovery from GY. Only problem they have is non-target removal and that's why it is a budget deck. Decode Talker, Transcode Talker, Rasterliger and Flame Administrator are simply to offer ATK boost incase you run into a destruction immune boss monster. Firewall Dragon is cumbersome to summon but if you have Will Of The Salamangreat and Sanctuary on the field, you can summon Sunlight Wolf on top of itself to revive the second copy from GY and go into Firewall Dragon easily. It offers non-destruction removal in case you need it.

deck_excerpt: A combo-heavier version of tri-brigade that fully utilizes the Crystal Beast engine. Plays well through interruptions and has an excellent grind game.
deck_description: Crystal Beasts, Tri-Brigades, and Albaz have a myriad of synergies with each other that this deck aims to exploit.  The Crystal Beast engine adds level 4 Beasts to the field and beasts/dragons to the hand, generating a ton of card advantage but lacking a clear way to exploit that advantage.  Tri-Brigades use those beasts on field to advance their plays and use the extra cards added to hand from Crystal Beast Rainbow Dragon to pay costs of cards like Tri-Brigade Bearbrumm, Tri-Brigade Ferrijit, and Tri-Brigade Kerass. These are the monsters that create the big plays and provide much of the grind game.  Tri-Brigade Mercourier, when banished, can add one of several cards from your deck to hand. Most often, you will often grab Albion the Shrouded, whose effect sends Branded Blade from Deck to grave in order to draw and add Mercourier back to hand. When in hand, it functions as a monster negate when you have an Albaz on the field  Branded in High Spirit converts a beast/dragon in hand into any of your albaz-related monsters - most often you'll grab Springans Kitt which can then special summon itself and grab Branded in Red or Branded Condemnation. It will send either Brigand or Albion the Branded Dragon from extra deck to grave, which will supply you an additional interruption or follow-up.  Allure of Darkness either converts the Rainbow Dark Dragon into tangible advantage or triggers Tri-Brigade Mercourier (providing a +2 when used to add Albion the Shrouded)  Your typical going first play is to land on Verte + Bearbrumm on field with mercourier in hand, then use Verte to send Branded Fusion to grave, fusing Albaz from deck with the Bearbrumm on field into Mirrorjade the Iceblade Dragon.  Then Bearbrumm will add Revolt to your hand. If you opened branded in high spirits, this can be further backed up with Branded in Red (for Guardian Chimera) and/or Branded Condemnation, leaving you with a board of 5-6 interruptions all coming from different places and a ton of cards added to your hand on the opponent's turn for turn 3 to guarantee you win the duel.

deck_excerpt: Use the Virus to your advantage and destroy your opponents deck from the inside before they get a chance to do anything.
deck_description:
Here's my list and reasoning for the cards within this deck.
  • Darkest Diablos is a solid Boss monster with 3000 attack and with his effect of a summon from hand or graveyard as long as you tribute one of your monsters, I feel this accompanies the deck very well.
  • Ahrima is a great card since it can search deck for Lair of Darkness and combos if lair of darkness is on the field can use its effect to tribute an opponents monster or one of your monsters for a draw or search from the deck.
  • Both Tenyi Monster's (Vishuda and Ashuna) are great since you can summon them for free as long as you control no effect monsters and with solidified defense which will more likely be used alongside the virus trap cards. Not Only that but this deck does run Monk of the Tenyi and Mystery Shell Dragon which combo with the tenyi monster effects from field and graveyard.
  • Mystery Shell dragon is a Normal Monster with a solid 2000 attack which can be used for the virus cards and it's also a Wyrm type monster which can be used to summon Shaman of the Tenyi.
  • Mask of Darkness was originally a joke since yknow we wear mask during the Pandemic to face off a virus.... but it's effect cycles trap cards which is good for a Trap deck like this.
  • Tribe-Infecting Virus, I was originally going to run 3 of these but I only have 1 in the collection lol and 6$ for one is pretty expensive. You could interchange mask of darkness for the other two if you choose too. ( Listen only because you can afford hefty cards and 6$ isn't a lot doesn't mean we lower class don't exist)
  • Dust Kaiju is just an overall good card since it tributes one of your opponents monsters so you could get rid of some annoying cards. Plus this can combo with Lair of Darkness and a virus card if you were to summon a kaiju on your opponent field you could use a virus to tribute the same kaiju since lair of darkness allows you to tribute opponent monsters.
  • Lilith is a trap card search so you basically guarantee a virus in the hand as long as you have her on the field.
  • Eldlich is just a great card since he can summon himself after a long process, not necessarily great but he could some in clutch with the attack stats.
  • Recurring Nightmare cycles lilith, mystery shell, and Ahrima which is always great since they all have they're purposes.
  • Allure of Darkeness is +1 and this deck is full of dark type monsters so it shouldn't be a big problem.
  • The Fang of Critais summons doom virus dragon which has a crush card virus type of effect which is good plus if you so happen too you can use it as material for a virus card.
  • I shouldn't have to explain Lair of Darkness this deep in.
  • Cosmic Cyclone is one of the few spell and trap negates in the deck which is why I chose the banish effect over MST or Twin Twisters.
  • All the virus cards are what run the deck which is why the monsters either have strong attack or strong defense, The weaker virus cards though have more copies since I feel those cards are more accessible in requirements compared to the stronger virus cards like grinning grave and eradicator virus
  • Aight so Originally the deck ran Imperial Order, Got absolutely yeeted into the ban list soooo changed it to solemn strike for monster negate but like always you can switch this out for another cosmic cyclone.
  • Monk of Tenyi is a Normal Monster to combo with the tenyi, Shaman is a good monster card especially the effect is has with the other wyrm and tenyi monsters which is why she's in here. Berserker legit cause why not lol.
Overall that's it if you made this far, Thank you for taking your time. Made this deck because we are in a pandemic and got inspired to make a virus deck. I know the deck is a joke but the real virus isn't please everyone be safe out there and please wear a mask. If you haven't gotten vaccinated please do, I can't force you to so if you don't want too that's up to you. -Kish

deck_description: Oh boy time to type. This deck isn't meant to be an s-tier deck but instead goes to show how broken Crystron Halqifibrax is. I am not against long combos but this is just an issue. Someone can make a deck that is much more consistent, powerful, less vulnerable to hand traps, and end with an even more broken board.  (Joker voice) "It's not about winning, It's about sending a message." Normal summon Deep Sea Diva, special summon Gutiar Gunards Duonigis, increase the level of Deep Sea Diva by two, Synchro summon Yazi, pop Yazi and special summon Mare Mare, Use Mare Mare's effect twice to make 2 tokens, tribute 1 token and Mare Mare to link summon Halquifibrax, use Halqifibrax's effect to special summon Ash Blossom, Synchro summon Cupid Pitch using 1 token and Ash Blossom, Search out Hero Kid using Cupid Pitch, special summon Dynatherium from your hand, Synchro summon Junk Speeder using Cupid Pitch and Dynatheruim, special summon Quickdraw Synchron 2 Fleur Synchrons and Steam Synchron, Synchro summon Red Supernova Dragon using the 2 Fleur Synchrons Steam Synchron and Junk Speeder, Special summon Hero Kid using the effect of Fleur Synchron, use the effect of Hero Kid to special summon 2 copies of itself from the deck, synchro summon Trishula using Quickdraw Synchron and 2 Hero Kids to banish 1 card from your opponent's hand field and gy, Link summon Verte Anaconda using Halqifibrax and Hero Kid, Use the effect of Verte Anaconda to copy the Effect of Red-Eyes Fusion and fusion Summon Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon. Congratulations, You now have an 8000  attack beatstick that can't be destroyed by your opponent's card effects, an Omni-negate and a once monster destruction, and have banished 1 Card from your opponent's hand, field, and gy while having a reusable banish all of your opponent's cards. IsN't ThAt FuN!

deck_excerpt: Number 88: Gimmick Puppet of Leo master race
deck_description: This deck as the main purpose of winning with number 88's effect and defending him as much as possible. The field spell guarantees to number 88 to survive during battle phase, "Condolence Puppet" avoids the possibility to having n. 88 destroyed by card effects. Trap cards can counter most of the combos, if positioned correctly. Barrier Statue can also stop most of the combos from meta decks with types different from the Dark one. Gigantes doll can steal 2 of the opponent's monsters, and you can use those monsters as xyz materials for n. 88. I also added others rank 8 dark monsters to defend number 88 from effects.  This deck was designed only by me, trying to improve n. 88 true potential with lots of counters. Idk if it's a valuable meta deck, but I will test it on Master Duel, since it just came out.  If it's a very strong deck against the current meta, I'll update the category of this deck in "Meta Deck". Probably I'll also make some future changes, to make it more balanced and strong. I'll try my best.

deck_excerpt: A fine, budget Eldlich deck to farm the ladder, if you can handle a miserable grind game for a while before building a deck that you actually wanna pl
deck_description: Hi, it's me again, Grayewick the Fusion strategy enjoyer, back with a budget list of one of the most common decks right now in the Master Duel ladder, Eldlich. I normally wouldn't suggest this deck to anyone at all, including Sky Strikers not because they're bad, but for various reasons I do not wish to state, especially if you already have a deck in mind in which you are confident enough that you can actually pilot competently enough, but the only reason as to why I do is simply because of how easy it is to obtain and pilot, and how it interacts with the low rarity staples in the game. Also, Eldlich is technically a Fusion strategy, except we don't really have the Seven Cities of the Golden Land to fuse yet (correction, we do already have it, it's just that Eldlich, the Mad Golden Lord is another UR that you'd have to pull/craft, so unless you're dedicated to Eldlich, I don't recommend building using it), but anyway. I made this list as free to play as possible, and with the assumption that you've already done the basic free to play routine at this point in the game. Addressing the deck list: • x3 Forbidden Chalice into x3 Forbidden Droplet = Forbidden Droplet, alongside Solemn Judgment, are probably two of the most easily obtainable and most powerful staples in the game, hands down. You can easily unlock it buy either crafting a random UR/SR "Forbidden" or "Darklord" card to unlock the "Deceitful Wings of Darkness" Secret Pack, where you can farm it there by unlocking packs and get crafting materials. What this also allows you to do is to pivot into the Darklord strategy, if that interests you in any way, shape, or form, or just as an investment for future support/archetype releases that might have synergy with it, such as Despia. • x3 Horn of Heaven and x1 Solemn Judgment into x3 Solemn Judgment and x1 Imperial Order = Pretty self-explanatory. You can easily unlock Solemn Judgment by either crafting a random UR/SR "Parshath" or "Agent" card to unlock the "Guardians of the Sacred Sky" Secret Pack, where you can farm it there by unlocking packs and get crafting materials. What this also allows you to do is to pivot into the Counter Fairies strategy, a classic control deck that focuses mainly on the small Fairy-type monsters that gain effects upon activating a Counter Trap, which also has great synergy with Eldlich. I have also made a list for that if it interests you in this link: https://ygoprodeck.com/counter-fairy-eldlich-master-duel/ • x3 Bottomless Trap Hole and x3 Ice Dragon's Prison = These two, you can actually decide to play together if you want, in any ratio you see fit. • x3 Lost Wind into x3 Infinite Impermanence = I'm actually on the fence between these two, because they both have their own strengths and weaknesses. The former being not minding getting discarded for Eldlich or Forbidden Droplet, and the latter essentially being used to either lock down a column from Spells or as a defensive tool going second. I'll leave this one up to your personal preference. • x1 Number 61: Volcasaurus into x1 Constellar Pleiades = Good enough boss monster with a non-destruction quick play interruption, while the former is a monster spot removal but worse. More budget options: • Heavy Storm Duster (SR) - This is considered a budget option due to a play set of this being guaranteed to be available in the "Magician of Pendulum" Structure Deck. Buy with caution. • Fiendish Chain/Phantom Knights' Fog Blade (R) - Both monster interruptions that stay on the field. • Dark Core (R) - Outs monsters that cannot be destroyed by card effects but can still be targeted. Also a discard enabler. • Floodgate Trap Hole (R) - Great against swarm and Pendulum decks, or just non-Link boss monsters that are pretty difficult to out. • Dust Tornado (R) - Back row removal and potential set up. • Raigeki Break (R) - Generic spot removal and discard enabler. • Ballista Squad (R) - Generic spot removal and enables Lightning Storm if you decide to play it. • Magic Jammer/Magic Drain/Divine Wrath (R) - Generic Counter Traps that are also discard enablers. • Light-Imprisoning Mirror/Shadow-Imprisoning Mirror (R) - Attribute related floodgates. • Trap Jammer (N) - Also a generic Counter Trap, could be nice on mirror matches. The extra deck is pretty self-explanatory being filled with either Dogmatika Punishment targets or Pot of Prosperity fodders. Make use of Psy-Framelord Omega, Elder Entity N'tss, and Wind Pegasus @Ignister as soon as you get hold of them. Super Polymerization can also be a cute tech, in case you run into Eldlich mirror matches. That's pretty much everything there is to it.

deck_description: If u have big budget u can replace upstart goblin and pot of desire with x2 pot of prosperity and if u want u can replace Windwich engine with Enforcer package but personally i like more windwich engine - crystal wing is very strong and cannot be destroyed by card effects (thanks to snow bell) also the eff of wind pegasus can be used to destroy spell/trap the same turn (before the summoning of crystal wing). Anyway, If u replace windwich engine with Enforcer package  also is ok if u have the budget. Both engines are killer. Personally i like the windwich engine because is not expensive and is working very well with both invoked or dogmatika engines.  About Maximus: Everyone using 1 copy of maximus (me also in the past) but that's wrong, Maximus x3 is the best. Normal summon whatever monster (even hand trap), summon almiraj - gardna - sp summon maximus - send in gy apcalone and ash dragon - set schism for winda - sp summon ecclesia in EP by ash dragon and add fleur in your hand. I mention that combo because the most of the people thinks Maximus is brick or bad draw, but is not.  About Windwich engine: Sp summon Windwich ice bell and use eff - sp summon glass bell and use eff - add snow bell and sp summon it from hand - summon wind pegasus using glass bell and ice bell - summon crystal wing using pegasus and snow bell. The same turn u can normal summon Aleister for Raidjin or normal summon ecclesia (search by nadir) to add fleur in hand. Note: if u have both Maximus and Ice Bell in hand then u have to choice between Maximus combo or windwich combo, if your choice is for Maximus then normal summon Ice Bell (or other monster) and summon Almiraj - Gardna - etc... With enforcer package u will not be able to choice between maximus combo or Enforcer except if u don't have other appropriate monster in hand for almiraj, that's why personally i like more windwich engine because i have choice and it doesn't play bricks.  Small World is searcher for invoked and dogmatika engines, also for windwich.

deck_excerpt: Book of Taiyou, jars, fusions, etc.. Progression series deck 9
deck_description: Using Book of Taiyou, it's possible to set flip effect monsters and activate their powerful effects in main phase 1. This includes morphing jar, which allows you to draw a new hand and forces your opponent to do the same, cyber jar, which destroys all monsters and mills 5 cards which are either summoned or sent to your hand, and dice jar, which deals up to 6000 damage to your opponent (but can backfire). The rest of the deck is just removal, negation, churning through the deck, and getting powerful fusion summons, including Last Warrior From Another Planet, who prevents summons. Book of Taiyou isn't considered a flip summon, so this allows you to set cards and flip them into attack position even under his effect.  9th deck made in a progression series after drawing 48 of every set before Invasion of Chaos, but using post-errata cards and the February 2004 ban list.

deck_description: This deck focuses on getting fusion materials and spells to the hand as quickly as possible and getting large damage in very quickly. There's removal to deal with opponent's monsters, spells, and traps, and plenty of revival for when your powerful fusion dies.  5th deck made in a progression series after drawing 48 of every set before Pharaonic Guardian, but using post-errata cards and no ban list. This is the tournament winning deck (5 person tournament).

deck_excerpt: Focused on C15 and C40 effects, and defending those monsters from the current meta
deck_description: DECK UPDATE #1 [23/01/22] As a gimmick puppet enjoyer, I decided at first to create a balanced Gimmick Puppet Deck that could go against the current meta, especially on Master Duel. As someone remembers, I tried yesterday to focus this deck on defending Number 88 and winning with its effect, but I couldn't really find a good way to summon always him in the beginning of a duel; I'm not saying that it's a bad card, but it's just not so easy to summon in the first turns (and that's why I put him in the Side Deck). So I decided to give more space to the other Gimmick Puppet numbers, such as c15 and c40, because they can help you out to get rid of most of the opponent's card in the field. And to help them out some defenses are required: -"Condolence Puppet" grants to c15 and c40 to survive against cards as Raigeki (which is kind of popular in Master Duel); -"Heavy Metal Raiders" (the Field Spell) can keep in battle every g. puppet monster that you have in the field, which is kind of dope (idk why no one talked about this card already but whatever); -"Infinite Impermanence" and "Broken Line" can block most of the combos (I used those against a Blue Eyes deck and I was laughing my ass off); -"Debunk" can negate Ash Blossom's effect, and that's cool; -"Network Trap Hole" can also block Summon Combos, especially the ones that use the main deck or the GY; - "Mythical Space Typhoon" I think it's almost needed in every deck, can destroy a lot of annoying cards (especially Field ones); -"Number 23" and "Dingirsu, the Orcust of the Evening Star" are the best boys in this deck, they can negate effects and prevent the destruction of your cards by opponent card's effects. I also kept "Barrier Statue of the Abyss" in this deck, because I find interesting his effect; I honestly discovered his existence some days ago, and for now I couldn't find a duel where this card saved me from enemy combos, so if this card keeps being useless, I'll decide to remove it from this deck, and maybe replace it with an another monster. And as Rank-Up card, I think that "Rank-Up-Magic Numeron Force" is the best choice among the others, because you can negate all face-up card's effects permanently, which is kind of sick, but at the same time this card could be your doom if you use it incorrectly, so think carefully when you should use it. With those things said, I'll continue my research on creating the ultimate Gimmick Puppet Meta deck, and if I succed in my goal, I'll put this deck in the "Meta" category. If you suggest some other cards to put in this deck, or if you think that some of those cards are useless, please write your opinion in the comments, so that we could bring gimmick puppets in the meta togheter. See you in the next  update.   Rasputin

deck_excerpt: Master Duel Deck out of Fun
deck_description:
As I said before... this ain't an meta deck or a deck focusing on competitive duels. This deck also mainly focuses on it's  archetype "Black Rose Dragon" aka. "Rose". So how do I use this deck? First of all you have to know that the main engine of this archetype is to destroy the whole field of cards via card effects (for example: Black Rose Dragon/Ruddy Rose Dragon). To deal damage to your opponent, you have to special summon monsters from your Extra Deck or Graveyard such as Black Rose Dragon to activate it's effects, which allows the user to target one of the opponent's monster and to change it's atk to 0 ... basicially a mix between destruction and damage dealing. In this case, the player has to summon Synchro Monsters (either from the Graveyard {by the effects of Blue Rose Dragon or Basal Rose Shoot/Black Garden} or from the Extra Deck {via. synchro summon or the effects of monsters such as Ruddyrose Dragon/Crossrose Dragon}). It does not sound easy, right? Well the thing is, that this deck is kinda outdated, especially with only one way of negating effects (Ruddy Rose Dragon). So instead of showing you a way to play a meta deck, I will show you the probably fastest and easiest way of summoning destructive and fearless Monsters Monster Cards: In this deck we use a mix of main deck monsters and extra deck monsters (especially main deck monsters as tuning materials)
  • Rose Dragons: mainly used as fast synchro materials and to search out supportive spells and traps (feat. the "Rose" archetype)
  • Plant Monsters: used as synchro or link materials, also used as cards to either search out other plant monsters or to special summon plant tokens on the field
Spell Cards:
  • Quick-Play Spell Cards: mainly used to special summon several Rose Dragons (either from the hand or graveyard) or to search out possible extra deck materials
  • Field Spell Cards: mainly used to either boost up your Rose Synchro Dragon or to special summon it by tributing plant monsters on the field (they are in generell plant tokens)
Trap Cards:
  • mainly used to summon out plant tokens or to protect or your monsters by banishing them temporarily
I hope that little description did help you to understand the function of this deck. The rest is either to train with or to modificate it.
