deck_name: Charmer / Familiar-Possessed 2022 Eda the Sun Magician build
deck_excerpt: Charmer / Familiar-Possessed aggro-stun pure deck build. Powerful pure deck build synergy featuring Eda the Sun Magician and versatile extra deck tool
deck_description: This deck was built to take full advantage of the whole Charmer / Familiar-Possessed archetype including spells and traps introduced in the Structure Deck: Spirit Charmers. After playing with different deck builds for several months it's become clear that the field spell Grand Spiritual Art - Ichirin plays a HUGE role to being able to stun and slightly slow down opponents just enough for Charmers/Familiar Possessed to slightly build a board. This Deck is not at all meta nor the next tier 1 YET it becomes really fun after a learning curve. Spells and Traps are the backbone of this deck and Awakening of the Possessed forms are kept in the deck to help search "Possessed" Spell/Traps on top of being able to be special summoned from the Deck with their unique effects.     The purpose of the deck is to be a stun/control deck revolving around Grand Spiritual Art - Ichirin and Eda the Sun Magician. Having Grand Spiritual Art -Ichirin up on the field is VERY important to begin stunning and board building because [1] Grand Spiritual Art -Ichirin negates your opponent's first monster effect as long as a Spellcaster monster with 1500 DEF is up on the field and [2] Grand Spiritual Art -Ichirin allows you to push back any Charmer / Familiar-Possessed from hand into the deck to help search for a smaller form of the Awakening of the Possessed monsters (This is a HUGE deal because if you control a Spellcaster monster you can special summon any of the smaller forms from the hand). Eda the Sun Magician's role in this build is VERY important because not only does Eda the Sun Magician fulfill Grand Spiritual Art - Ichirin's requirement to be able to negates your opponent's first monster effect, when normal summoned or flipped-up, Eda the Sun Magician grants a special summon of 1 Spellcaster from hand or Deck in face-down defense position AND Eda the Sun Magician's quick effect allows for a disruption of opponents board building by being able change 1 face-down Spellcaster from defense to face-up Attack OR Defense Position. This essentially puts 2 negates up on the board if the proper Charmer is flipped face-up to steal an opponent's monster.     Spirit Charmers is the important to be able to search any of the "Charmer" monsters. "Familiar-Possessed" monsters, and/or "Possessed" Spells/Traps including Unpossessed. 3 copies of this card is without a doubt necessary for any Charmer/Familiar-Possessed pure deck build. Ideally, Spirit Charmers should be used to help set up backrow to synergy the whole board. A synergized Charmer/Familiar-Possessed board of this pure build should have Grand Spiritual Art - Ichirin, Awakening of the Possessed, and Unpossessed all active at once with at least 1 Charmer monster face up in defense position.     Awakening of the Possessed is the main draw engine and helps beef up all monsters you control by 300 ATK for each different attribute you control. This help clear the board with Familiar-Possessed monsters often times having enough ATK to get through most monsters AND Awakening of the Possessed also helps protect Charmers / Familiar-Possessed monsters from being destroyed by card effects.     Unpossessed is the main protection for Charmers. When Unpossessed is up Charmer monsters you control can not be destroyed by battle. Not only that but Unpossessed helps boost Familiar-Possessed monsters by giving them an additional 800 ATK when attacking an opponent's monster. On top of all of that whenever a monster you control is destroyed by battle or card effect; Unpossessed lets you special summon a 1 Spellcaster with 1500 DEF from your deck in Attack Position or face-down Defense position.     Possessed Partnerships for this build is a 3 and here is why. Possessed Partnerships allows you to special summon 1 Spellcaster monster with 1500 DEF from your hand or GY in attack position or face-down position, then, if you control monsters with 2 or more different attributes you can destroy 1 face-up card on the field. Depending on how the board looks often times this card is used to destroy 1 face-up card on the field primarily backrow or field spell YET the purpose of this card as well is to help keep a Spellcaster with 1500 DEF up on the field to reap full effects of Grand Spiritual Art - Ichirin. BUT the main purpose of having Unpossessed at 3 is due to its graveyard effect allowing it to be banished to target a "Possessed"/"Unpossessed" continuous Spell/Trap in your GY to then place it face-up on your field. Essentially having Possessed Partnerships in the graveyard helps set up your board     Magician's Right Hand is here to make opponent spend resources. (This card usually helps force opponent to deal with it)  This card can easily be swapped out depending on opponent's deck build. Solemn Judgment and Magician's Left Hand serve a similar purpose and are usually swapped in when facing Eldlich decks.     Pinpoint Guard is just there to help bring back a Charmer / Familiar-Possessed. Primarily Charmers to help re-establish board lock on next turn. Fairy Tail - Luna can be swapped in to help bounce opponent's monsters on the field and help synergize with Awakening of the Possessed draw engine. Fairy Tail - Luna also synergizes with Grand Spiritual Art - Ichirin's deck searching effect.     Night's End Sorcerer is new to the build. Night's End Sorcerer was added to gain access to Synchro toolbox of Levels 5, 6, and 7 due to main deck staples running 4 level 3, 4 level 4, and 4 level 5 monsters, not counting Eda the Sun Magician. Nights End Sorcerer is very neat to the build and can really help stun if used to bring out Clear Wing Synchro Dragon (Pretty much a mini Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon).     Hope you enjoy!!

deck_excerpt: A new version of my favorite deck, made for winning!
deck_description: So, the last and the strongest version! I again found some cards that would make it better, and here it is! The deck contains:  Main:  3 Luster Dragon- Here only as a material for "Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon"  3 Nexus- Banish 4 opponent's monsters from GY to be special summoned, destroys all ATK position extra deck monsters, AND inflicts 800 damage for each destroyed. Ideal if your opponent plays Invoked.  3 Fleurdelis- Very easy to special summon, negates effects of an extra deck monster and makes all Dogmatikas gain 500 ATK.  3 Ashyan- Easy to summon, adds a monster from the GY to the hand, and makes all Dogmatikas gain 500 ATK.  3 Theo- Easy to summon, cannot be destroyed by battle and transfers 600 ATK from an opponent's monster to itself.  3 Ecclesia- Literally does 70% of support to a whole deck.  3 Adin- Easy to summon, special summons a Dogmatika monster from the deck.  3 Shaddoll Beast- Requires 1 tribute to be set, +1 if flips, and +1 more if destroyed by effect.  3 White Knight- You cannot summon extra deck monsters, but you can destroy an extra deck monster directly from each extra deck.  1 Cyber-Stein- Limited, so only one we get.  3 Dogmatikalamity- Used just to summon White Knight.  1 Nation- Only one because you can add it with "Terraforming". All dogmatikas are immune to the extra deck monsters' effects and destroy a battling monster instead of  themself.  1 Terraforming- Limited, so only one we can have.  1 Monster Reborn- Limited, so only one we can have.  3 Encounter- Not the best, but useful.  3 Infinite Impermanence- A cheap version of "Ash Blossom".  3 Genesis- Returns your banished Extra deck monster and negates opponent's.  3 Mirror force- if you go first and get this card, just set it and end turn. Then, your opponent will regret when he attacks you.  Extra:  1 Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon- Super broken and surely the best ever fusion monster.  1 Number 39: Utopia- Not really the best, but very easy to summon.  1 Divine Arsenal AA ZEUS- Sky Thunder- Easy to summon, has at least 2 Xyz materials when summoned, and does a "Black Hole" effect, saves itself  from it, and all of that with a price of just 2 Xyz materials.  1 Decode Talker- Super generic and very easy to summon, it is one of the cards that can level up every weak deck.  1 Decode Talker Extended- The same as the normal "Decode Talker", but stronger.  1 Accesscode Talker- Very generic, and also very strong. The upgraded version of previous two Talkers.  1 Predaplant Verte Anaconda- A very good fusion support for "Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon".  Side:  3 Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring- one of the best hand traps ever, screws pretty much everything.  3 Effect Veiler- Simply negates the effects of one monster.  3 Ghost Ogre- Say goodbye to that monster.

deck_excerpt: Dark Hole FTW
deck_description: You can switch Cardcar D with Cyber Valley for more stalling.  Summon either Sangan or Witch Of The Black Forest, use Dark Hole then search for one of the pieces.  Activate Allure Of Darkness at all costs, then banish either Sangan or Witch (you need Battle Fader for stalling).  Use Magical Mallet to get rid of cards you find unnecessary at any specific time during the duel.  Gold Sarcophagus can be used to either slim down the deck so you draw the pieces faster (in this case you banish any other monster that's not an Exodia piece) OR you can banish a piece of Exodia, use Burial From A Different Dimension to send it to your GY (another piece must be face up on the field at this given time), then use Dark Hole or Torrential Tribute to send the face up Exodia piece to the GY. Once this step is complete, you can activate Dark Factory Of Mass Production and retrieve both pieces. ONLY go for second route if you wanna retrieve the piece banished by the Sarcophagus the SAME turn it is banished. I'd do this if only one piece is remaining.

deck_excerpt: the combination you never wanted PUNK + MYUTANT, my obsession with myutant will always be present!
deck_description: ah yes, you read it right, what is the major problem with P U N K? it doesnt have a why to put a level 8 consistently or without it being fragile... I present to you a my first variant of this mix, it is still hard around the edges! so lots of room for improvement! also, play 3 teleport, i used 2 just to test it out on edo pro in rooms that would let me.... i didnt want to upload this with out playing with strangers!.  How good is it? its pretty consistent i do say so! it has bricks.... YES! but its fun it can play againtst backrow, and the combo with punks is enabled with:  Ze amin, search Fox lady, foxy tune discard + other send to grave; summon Sharakusai, if you have P U N K in hand fusion in a way you only leave Sharakusai on field (you need him to later synchro 11 on oponents turn with a level 8 myutant). Fusion tributes itsef and you summon form deck Madame spider + (insert any punk lvl3 ot Sharakusai if you used him). Search trap with Madem spider.  Halquifibrax for deskbot, Link 3 Aurorodon and later, 3 tokens, deskbot revives, go into cupid pitch, lower level to form 4 to 3, coral dragon, tribute coral + token with link 3 effect to summon Coltwing, your field should be 4 cards in hand, 2 tokens, Sharakusai, level 10 coltwing + Deskbot 01. (CUPID SEARCH PSYCHIC TRACKER)  with the deskbot you can go into a FA. Dawn dragster, or go for a shooting riser dragon (7*) with the 2 tokens (3+3+1). with shooting star send from deck to grave a level 1 and go to baroness. (for now this part sending a level 1 with nothing to use for it i still dont know what so i would love some help)  if this play started by special summoning Ze Amin with foxy first turn, or teleport, go on to your myutant plays, if you had to normal summon it, hopefully you drew the myutant field spell + a myutant. for now its been very consistent for me to put a the fullboard including a level 8 myutant + fleur + Sharakusai + link 3 and 1-2 facedowns, if you started with normal summon Ze amin but havent used your teleport, use teleport for myutatn combo.  MYUTANT COMBO IS ALWAYS LAST.

deck_excerpt: Master Duel Platinum grind deck
deck_description: This is the deck i climbed into Platinum with in Master Duel.  The deck is relatively cheap to make and easy to pick up and learn.     Just a few pointers. deck_excerpt: @Ignister Deck profile  Master Duel Platinum 1
deck_description:
Hello this is my Master Duel @Ignister deck profile. I reached plat 1 with it. I'll go over the basic combo + end board. The basic endboard is basically, a 4k Arrival Cyberse + an unaffected Cyberse Quantum Dragon. How to get there through a 1 card combo: Normal summon Achichi --> add Pikari Link achichi for Infant --> Infant adds AI Land Activate AI Land --> summon pikari through AI land Pikari adds AI meet you --> activate ai meet you AI meet you adds Doyon --> Link Pikari and Infant for Cyberse Wicckid Activate AI Land to summon Doyon to a zone Wicckid points to --> CL1 Doyon, CL2 Wicckid. Doyon adds back the monster you've normal summoned, which in our case is Achichi. Wicckid banishes Infant and adds us Bururu. --> Link of Doyon + Wicckid for Transcode Talker --> activate AI land and summon Bururu, you must avoid the zone Transcode Talker points to, since we're using Transcode Talker's effect --> Bururu sends Gatchiri to the GY --> Transcode Talker activates its effect to summon back Wicckid --> Link the 3 units away for Dark Templar --> Activate AI land yet again to summon Achichi -->link away Achichi for Infant, Infant must be summoned to the left most zone of Templar --> activate Templar's effect, CL1 Templar, CL2 Infant --> Change Infant's attribute to Divine and summon three units through Templar's effect --> The three units you will be summoning are: Achichi, Bururu, Pikari, --> Synchro summon, Pikari + Bururu for Cyberse Quantum Dragon --> Activate Bururu's effect to summon back Pikari --> Link Achichi + Pikari for Splash Mage --> Activate Splash mage's effect to summon Gatchiri --> Make Arrival Cyberse with every unit except for Cyberse Quantum Dragon --> Activate Gatchiri effect targetting Cyberse Quantum Dragon to make him unaffected by your opponent's card effects till the end of their turn So, now we have 2 unaffected units, one of them protecting the other. If your opponent attacks Cyberse Quantum Dragon (which they must in order to out Arrival Cyberse) you can activate it's effect to bounce back that monster. This is basically not outable in Master Duel, since the only popular counter are Kaiju's and nobody runs Kaiju's in a 1 game format. I run 1 Crossout Designator as well as 2 Called by the Graves to out possible hadntraps. The limitation on Crossout in Master Duel is super annoying. I've considered running Sauravis as a replacement for atleast Veiler/Imperm, but I do not think it's worth it.

Pros and Cons Pros deck: -Very easy to OTK -Good end board -Unexpected, not many people know what @Ignisters do. I had tons of people try and out the unaffected Cyberse Quantum Dragon through stuff like Raigeki, which obviously does not work, but since people don't know what @ignisters do and don't read cards, it's basically a free win. -Genuinely fun to play Cons: -Susceptible to handtraps especially Nibiru, that's why the Crossout's + Called by's are so important.

deck_name: Mater Duel Trick Star Deck January 2022
deck_excerpt: When you wanna be the most annoying person turn 1 on master duel but wanna be fairly F2P, well here's the deck for you. This deck was built during the
deck_description:
!WARNING! This deck runs 3 Pot of Desires but because Master Duel runs on this weird banlist I had to replace it with another pot of card. So if you're making it in Master Duel, 3 pot, if you're doing this in Omega or the real OCG, you might have to run another draw card. !WARNING! ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- The FTK aspect of this deck can be simplified to this. You need either 2 dark room of nightmare or dark room and 1 light stage mixed with a continue, in the case of 2 desires that would be a live stage, in the case of light stage, festival and magical lauriel would be the most optimal thing to add to hand, but this option is a bit rough as you have to focus even more on placement of tokens as to optimally squeeze all the effect damage out of holly angel. Ok, if you have either of these set ups the combo is simple
  1. Try to bait out Ash with canadina or one of your other special summons. If you can do this, you can set up the rest of your plays without the fear of interruption in 90% of cases. (If you often get screwed by nibiru you can switch out droll and called by for nibiru and crossout designator.)
  2. If you make it out alive, you can use your whatever extender you have, whether its Festival, or live stage, or another trick star to start setting up for the combo. Go into Bloom (Link 1) and then into Holly Angel if you know you will be safe. This way if you pull Magical Lauriel you will have a target that can assist you into another link monster.
  3. Heres where the magic happens. Link summon into everything you possibly can. But if you have a dead trickstar in your hand and feel like gambling, link into crimson heart and see what the luck of the draw gives you. You could get a good card like an extender, or you can get a dead card, like a nibiru or droll and lock.
  4. When you come to the point where you can make the link 4 you have 1 job. place Bella Madonna ANYWHERE that doesn't point to a monster. By this point Bella will do 1000-1600 damage on her own, which will probably be the FTK, and if not, they'll be really close.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Now know this deck can work through Ash blossom and does not only work as an FTK deck, Festival can protect Trickstars from destruction, Holly Angel gains attack everytime burn damage is inflicted, and you have some good turn 1 effects like Divaridis who if you go up against a heavy special summon deck its like playing with Maxx C but instead of maximum draw power, it's how much health will your enemy have at the end of your combo while Holly Angel is getting 200 attack every summon. So this is a decent Rogue deck with a really fun FTK to try out when the stars align.

deck_excerpt: Zombie World deck for Master Duel
deck_description: Decklist of my Zombie/Danger deck I play on Master Duel. How does this deck work? Here, we want to control the field. Zombie World is a powerful field that changes every monster(s) on the field and the GY into zombies. Some decks face huge problems with this (eg. Tri-brigade). You need that field ON as soon as possible. This is the heart of the deck. Now, let's talk about our boss monster: Balerdroch. Very easy to summon, once it's on the field it can negate zombies monsters' effects and banish one monster from play or graveyard. That makes him a difficult monster to deal with. That's why we need Zombie World: as opponent's monsters become zombies you can chain their effects with Balerdroch. Then, if you manage to draw "Rivalry of the Warlords" your victory is getting closer. What does Rivalry? Once on the field each player can control only 1 monster type. So, if Zombie World is ON, your opponent cannot summon from his hand/deck/extra-deck as long as he has a monster on his field that is zombie. A very powerful tool that locks completely your opponent. Key cards - Uni-Zombie: it's our combo starter. You can foolish a zombie monster from the deck and discard from the hand. Both effect once per turn. Targets: Banshee Necroworld, Mezuki, Gozuki, Glow-Up Bloom, Balerdroch... - Banshee Necroworld: By banishing it from the graveyard or field you can activate a "Zombie World" from your deck or hand. - Mezuki: by banishing it from the graveyard you can target one of your zombie monsters in the GY and special summon it. The good news here is that effect is not once per turn! - Solitaire Shiranui: Its role is to increase our chances to get Uni-Zombie in our first hand. By tributing a zombie monster (you can tribute that card) you can special summon a tuner/zombie monster from your deck. Target will usually be Uni-Zombie but you can search Glow-up Bloom as well if you need it. - Gozuki: Another combo starter but less powerful than Uni-Zombie. It can foolish from the deck too + if sent to the GY you can banish another monster in it and special summon a zombie monster from your hand. - Glow-Up Bloom: a tuner monster which role is to be sent to the graveyard in order to special summon a level 5 or more zombie monster on your field (if Zombie World is ON - otherwise you only get the card in your hand). Target : Balerdroch. Danger ! cards role The Danger archetype is here to make the deck more consistent. To make some 8 rank XYZ. To special summon some big monsters. To destroy some of your opponent's cards. To draw cards. Why 3 copies of Crossout? The deck is very sensitive to handtraps. Especially the most used one: Ash. If your opponent Ashes Uni-Zombie it will become difficult to start your combos. So, Crossout is here to protect you from Ash. Crossout can also prevent your opponent from using "Called by". That card is also a strong threat to the deck as it can banish and negate Balerdroch trying to return on the field. Another possibility is to negate for one turn Rivalry if you need to summon a non-zombie monster from your extradeck. What is the main combo of the deck? The Halqifibrax one. To make this combo we only need to activate Zombie World and have Uni-Zombie and another monster. Special summon Halqifibrax by sending Uni-Zombie and the second monster to the GY. Once Halqi is on the field activate its effect that allows you to special summon a tuner monster from your deck or hand. The target is: Glow-up bloom. At that point, depending on what you have in your hand, two scenarios: - If you still have Danger ! monster to play, extradeck monsters to summon that are not zombies, do not send Glow-up bloom to the GY until you didn't finish your other combos. Because Glow-up bloom will not allow you to special summon non-zombie monster for the rest of the turn if you used its effect. - If you don't have anything to do let's special summon Linkuriboh by using Glow-Up bloom. Once Glow-up Bloom is sent to the GY you can activate its effect and special summon Balerdroch. Use Balerdroch and your Linkuriboh to make Vampire Sucker. Then, end your turn. At the opponent's standbyphase you will revive your Balerdroch. That will trigger Vampire Sucker's effect: you draw 1 card. When your opponent summon a monster, activate Halqifibrax's effect: it will banish itself in order to summon a tuner synchro monster from your extradeck. Target: Formula Synchron. Once Formula Synchron hits the field you can activate its effect and draw 1 card. Formula Synchron has a second effect that allows you to perform a synchro summon during your opponent's turn. The target is Shiranui Sunsaga. Before doing this, be sure you used the effects of Balerdroch. Once Sunsaga is on the field you can at any moment return synchro zombie monster(s) that are in the GY or banished to your extradeck and destroy the same amount of cards your opponent controls. This combo if not interrupted by your opponent can lead you to an easy win. Have fun with this deck!

deck_excerpt: When people think of Utopia, they think of a pure OTK deck. Well not anymore!  (The Deck Description is the size of a Steven King novel, so make sure
deck_description: One of the first things you might notice, this deck has 45 cards. Feel free to remove 5, but I feel like it's better to have 5 extra cards. Utopia is a great deck. While it used to be an OTK tool with Utopia Double and Double or Nothing, it's now able to produce actual negates and good interactions. So lets do the card by card for the deck.  Main Deck.  The Onomat Trio: Utopic Onomatopoeia x2, Zubababancho Gagagacoat, and Dodododwarf Gogogoglove. These 3 cards are the main cards of the deck. If you can get 2 of these on board, you get a rank 4. If you get 2 of these on board and any other lvl 4, you can get 2 rank 4s. Zubababancho Gagagacoat can revive any Gogogo or Dododo in your graveyard, and Dodododwarf Gogogoglove can revive itself if you have another Gogogo/Dododo on your field. This means that you can cycle these level 4s every turn, mid combo, and when trying to rebuild a broken board.  The ZS's: ZS - Ascended Sage x2, ZS Armed Sage x2. These 2 ZS's allow for you to get free special summons and free cards. Ascended sage allows you to summon itself when you have no cards on field, and Armed sage when you have only 1 monster. But be very careful. If you activate a card like Onomatopickup, a continuous spell (I'll get to it in a minute,) You can't special summon Ascended Sage. But you can still normal it. And now take that same situation, you activate Pickup, then summon a lvl 4. Armed sage says "The only monster you control is a lvl 4 or lower" So even if you have a spell/trap on the field, it can be summoned.  Astral Cards: Astral Kuriboh x2 and Astraltopia x2 These 2 monsters are also free special summons, but with a few more restrictions. Astral Kuriboh allows you to reveal any Number in the extra deck, and summon it. Then its level is equal to it's rank. But guess what? It can be any level. While in Utopic, the only level you want to have it be is level 4, if you splash it into any other deck that plays numbers, you have a free summon of any level you need. When it is summoned, be careful. Because it Locks you into numbers while it's on the field. As soon it's used for an Xyz though, that lock goes away. In addition to being a free summon of any level, the monster you summon with Astral Kuriboh can't be destroyed by battle or card effect. So you can wall up with this card in a pinch. And Astraltopia, the better card. "If an Xyz monsters(s) is on the field: You can special summon this card from your hand." Notice how this is the Field, not your side of the field. In addition of that effect, it can send 1 card from the hand or field (which you have numerus targets to send, and yes, pun intended) to add one Xyz, Onomat, Zexal, or Number S/t from the deck to the hand. This means that if you go 2nd, you can summon this if the opponent has an xyz, possibly bait out a negate, and keep your normal summon. If not, you can still search MANY cards. As I go through the list, I'll point out the cards to search.  Onomat Spells: Onomatopaira x3, Onomatopickup x3. Onomatopaira allows you to discard 1, add any 2 cards from the Dododo/Gogogo/Gagaga/Zubaba archetype to the hand. This is probably one of the best searchers in all of yugioh. Most of the time, if you have a card from the Onomat trio in your hand, you search the other 2 cards in it and go full combo. If you don't you search Utopic Onomatopoeia (since it's treated as all of those cards) and Zubababancho Gagagacoat. You then normal summon the Utopic Onomat, and summon Bancho. If it's negated with a veiler or impermanence, you can use Bancho's effect in hand to summon it. If it's destroyed by a ghost ogre and snow rabbit, then you still summon Bancho, then revive Utopic Onomat. If it's negated AND destroyed, tough luck. And remember what I said about Paira being the best searcher? Onomatopickup is even better. In your starting hand, if you draw Zubababancho Gagagacoat and Dodododward Gogogoglove, but no Utopic Onomat, then you can use Pickup to search just that. No Discards. Side Note: These two cards are great search targets off of Astraltopia if you haven't normal summoned.  Reinforcement of the Army: Add any lvl 4 or lower warrior. It's a great searcher, and the only 2 targets we can't add are Dodododwarf Gogogoglove and Astral Kuriboh.  Zexal Construction x3: This card is amazing as well. (I've said that about 4 cards now I think.) It allows you to shuffle one of your garnets into the deck, or a useless card. Then you can add one of 5 archetypes, even though we aren't playing any Rank-Down-Magic cards. I'll also show you the garnets that you'll want to shuffle back with this.  Zexal Entrust x1: This card is mostly a search target for niche things. It's a great extender allowing you to summon a ZS from the gy, or a ZW if you want to buff your Xyz a little more. Summon a Utopia is only useful for one situation, which can only happen if you misplay in a BIG way. It also has a gy effect! If you're 2000 lp lower than your opponent, you can add another Zexal card from the gy to the hand. Our only target is Construction, but it is really good. Side Note: Great target to search with Construction & Astraltopia.  Hyper Rank-Up-Magic Utopiforce x1: Yes, that's the name. This card is searchable off of Construction and ZS Ascended Sage. This allows you to go into a 4 material Dragonar (Which I'll get to in a minute.) And when you summon an Xyz with a Utopia/Utopics effect, you get to attach this card to it as material. One of the best Rank-Up-Magic cards out there.  Numbers Protect x1: It's an Omni negate that is also a counter trap. It's searchable off of Astraltopia, and it has a gy effect to bring itself back. Need I say more?  Xyz Change Tactics x2: Pay 500 every Xyz summon of a Utopia, draw 1. No Once per turn. This card can be searched off of Astraltopia, and is a great way to set up for next turn.  Double or nothing x2: This is only useful for Utopia Double into Utopia for 10k damage, but otherwise, just a search target so Utopia Double can rank itself up.  The ZW's: Tornado Bringer, Lightning Blade, Pegasus Twin Saber x1. These can be searched by Construction, and by Armed Sage.  Tornado bringer allows you to equip it to a Utopia, and it gets 1300 atk with the ability to not be targeted. Lightning Blade gives it 1200 attack, and ZW's can't be destroyed. Pegasus Twin Saber can equip from the Field (keep that in mind) and give it 1000 attack. Pegasus has the additional effect to negate any monster effect that activates on the field. This can ignore chain blocking, and they can't respond to it since it doesn't activate. The only problem with this is that you have to either equip it from deck, or summon it. And it's a level 5 monster. It does have a way to summon itself though! If you're lp are 2000 lower than your opponents, you can summon it for free. This can be done with Xyz Change tactics, summon 4 Utopics. Which is actually really easy with the right hand.  Tech Cards: Called By the grave x1, Feather Duster x1, Monster Reborn x1: Called by the grave is a way to protect yourself from HT, since an ash blossom on a Paira will devastate you, essentially ending the turn. It's also a negate for GY decks. Feather duster for backrow, since the only other card we have is Tornado Dragon, meaning that a mystic mine when you don't have tornado is an FTK. it's also good for generic Backrow decks, like Eldlich (With 3 Skill Drain might I add) and Guru. Lastly, Reborn. The most common level in the game is level 4, and any level 4 and a reborn means you can go off from there. You can reborn one of your cards, one of your opponents, it's great.  Forbidden Droplet x2: This is a tech card, but it needs its own category. Utopia decks have a lot of cards that get used once and that's it. For example, you go full combo with an Xyz Change Tactics, you have Droplet. After going for a full combo, you'll only have a few Utopias left to summon, making Tactics a great target to send. Then you have the ZWs, good cards, but a Tornado Bringer isn't good against a deck that doesn't target. And you still have Onomatopickup, which has an on field effect only good for Tag Duels and if you summon a ZW. And the last card, Double Or Nothing, is useless after full combo. Since we're only playing 1 Number 39: Utopia, and full combo uses it for Dragonar, you can't use the Double or nothing in hand anymore.  HT: Ash Blossom x3, Infinite Impermanence x3: Ash is great, Impermanence is great. You can replace these with the HT of your choice, but my personal choice are these.     Extra Deck: Number 99: Utopia Dragonar x2. This is insane. Not just for Utopia, but for all number decks. When you do your combo, this has 4 materials. And it can use 2 materials to summon any 1 number that has a number between 1 and 100 in the text (So no, you can't make a iC1000 FTK deck.) as a quick effect. This means you can summon a card during your turn, then on the opponents. Targets for this include: Number 92: Heart-eartH Dragon, Number 38 hope Harbinger, Number 23, Lancelot, Dark Knight of the Underworld, Number 100; Numeron Dragon. I'll go over these cards seperately.  Number 92: Heart-eartH Dragon. For the millionth time, this card is insane. During the ep, detatch one, banish all cards your opponent controls that have been summoned or set this turn. Including s/t cards. If the opponent can't go through 3 negates, you can use this to kick them while they're down, and banish their floodgates, their traps, their Droplets. And if your opponent has a monster with high attack, and they have low lp, you can crash this into that monster and they take the damage. And on top of that, if it's destroyed by a card effect while it has xyz Material, which will almost never happen, it gets 1000 attack for every card that is banished. And if you're against a Swordsoul deck, or a Gren Maju deck that banished 3x Gren Maju, then you'll have just a few attack points to attack for lethal over the opponents 30k attack Gren Maju.  Number 38: Hope Harbinger. It's a spell negate, it's can attach a spell as Material. Great against Sky Striker decks, or any deck that use a lot of spells. And in a Mirror, you can attach an opponents Hyper Rank up Magic.  Number 23: Lancelot. This is a weird card. The first two effects it has are useless, so forget about those. This card is an omni negate. Nothing else to say about that. But it's a mandatory negate. If you  activate a card while it still has materials, you will be negating yourself. So be extra careful.  Numeron Dragon. This card needs no introduction. Detach one, gain a million atk. When summoning off of a Dragonar, this will have a minimum of 13000 attack. Compare that to Draglubion, making it 9k. Still a lot, but it almost never will OTK when the opponent is at 8k.  Leo Utopia Ray. It can detatch one, equip a ZW from the deck to itself. This allows it to become two negates. The first, by its own effect, being able to target a card on the field and negate and half its attack permanently. The 2nd negate is Pegasus Twin Saber, which we talked about earlier. You will only be getting the Pegasus twin saber, since you'll only have 1 material for it. If you drew the Pegasus twin saber, or are worried about targeted removal, get Tornado bringer.  Utopia Double x2; This card allows us to rank up into any Utopic monster in the extra deck. If we only have 2 level 4s, Utopia double into Leo will be good. For an OTK strategy, you can either go for Utopia Double into a Utopia for the classic 10k, or after the main combo, or if Hyper Rank up Magic is in the gy, you can Utopia double into a Dragonar, summoning a Numeron Dragon for 13k.  Number 39: Utopia. It allows us to go for a Dragonar, and OTK with a 10k beater.  Number S39: Utopia Prime. The Effect miiiggght be used, but almost never. The only other use is Dragonar, giving it another material. You can replace this with C39: Utopia Ray.  Tornado Dragon. This allows us to get 1. a Non-number rank 4 onto the field (you'll see why) and some free s/t removal.  ZS - Utopic Sage. This allows us to summon a ZS to the field, and in extension, add any Rank up magic or ZW to hand It's also the 2nd non number rank 4. Why would we need non number rank 4s?  Utopic Future & Utopic Future Draco. These cards can be built into the main combo. Utopic Future allows us to steal a monster the opponent controls for the battle phase, and Future Draco is a monster negate and it's able to take control of a negated monster effect if it's on the field.  Side Deck: You can do anything for it, but my personal choice is to have a Number 89 in there, along with ht and Mystic Mine hate.  Number 89: Diablosis the Mind Hacker. Its good for decks that rely on one card in their extra deck that they only have one of. Also FTK decks, but that's a niche use.  Nibiru: Going 2nd tool against ss decks.  Gameciel: Good against tower decks, could possibly replace this with Evenly.  Lancea: Good for banish decks like Swordsoul.  Token Collector: Good against Swordsoul and Brave Token decks.  Droll & Lock Birb: Good for decks that search the entire deck.  The Mystic Mine hate: This deck is mostly for casual, but is still good for meta play. And before you ask, Cursed Seal of the Forbidden Spell is a card I chose to put in there on purpose.        The Combos.  Ascended Sage Combo: End board = Leo Utopia Ray, Pegasus twin saber, Dragonar, Lancelot, and a Hear-eartH/Number 38 on the opponents turn.  Starting hand must include: A way to get to any of the 2 Onomat trio + ZS Ascended sage.  Summon Ascended Sage.  Summon the 2 Onomat Trio.  If the two cards are:  Utopic Onomatopoeia & Dodododwarf: Use Dodododwarf + ZS Ascended Sage for a Utopia Double. Use double, add Rank Up Magic Utopiforce, use Double again, detach Dodododwarf, go into a Leo. Use Dwarf effect in the GY, summon it back.  Utopic Onomatopoeia & Zubababancho: Use Onomatopoeia + ZS Ascended Sage for a Utopia Double. Use double, add Rank Up Magic Utopiforce, use Double again,  detach Onomatopoeia, go into a Leo. Use Coat effect, summon the Onomatopoeia back.  Dodododwarf & Zubababancho: Use Dodododwarf + ZS Ascended Sage for a Utopia Double. Use double, add Rank Up Magic Utopiforce, use Double again,  detach Dodododwarf, go into a Leo. Use Coat effect, summon the Dwarf back.  Use the 2 level 4s to go into a Utopia, use Utopia to go into Utopia Prime, then use Utopiforce to go into Dragonar. Before using Dragonar, use Leos effect to equip Pegasus twin saber to it as material. Now use Dragonar, summon the Number 23, Lancelot. Use Utopiforce in gy to attach itself as material. During the opponents turn, wait until they activate something and Lancelot negates to use Dragonar. Summon Number 38, or Heart-eartH dragon during the ep, depending on what deck you think they have.  Main Combo: This one's a doozy. End board: Leo Utopia Ray, Pegasus Twin Saber, Dragonar with 2 materials, and Utopic Draco Future.  Starting hand: A way to get to all 3 of the Onomat Trio.  Summon Utopic Onomat, use the effect, summon Dwarf and coat from your hand.  Use Utopic Onomat & Dwarf to go into ZS - Utopic Sage.  Use Sage effect, summon ZS - Ascended Sage.  Use Coat effect, summon Utopic Onomat.  Use Dwarf effect in gy, ss itself.  Use any of the onomat cards and Ascended Sage, go into Number 39: Utopia.  Use Effect, add Utopiforce.  Go into Utopia Prime.  Use Utopiforce, summon Dragonar.  Use Dragonar, summon Leo.  Use Utopiforce in gy: Attach to Leo.  Use the other 2 level 4s on the field, go into Tornado Dragon.  Use tornado dragon + Utopic Sage. Go into F0 Utopic Future. Then go into F0 Utopic Future Draco.  Use Leo, equip Pegasus Twin Saber.  This gets you 3 monster negates, and then either an Omni Negate, a Spell negate that you can do multiple times during the duel, and then a Heart-eartH dragon at the end phase.  Small Side note for main combo: If you have a way to get all 3 of the Onomat trio + Astraltopia, you can go even further beyond.  You do the main combo, but when you get to the part where you summon Utopic Sage, instead summon Utopia Double.  Then use Double to go into leo, use leo to make sure you still have the two Onomats in the grave.  Then summon them back with Coat and the gy effect of Dwarf, then summon Utopic Sage now.  Use sage, summon Ascended sage, then do the Dragonar line with Utopia, Utopia Prime, and Utopiforce.  Before activating Dragonar though, summon the Astraltopia, and use the effect sending the Double or nothing searched by utopia Double to add Zexal Entrust.  Now use Dragonar, and make sure to detatch ZS - Ascended Sage, and go for a number 38. Activate Entrust, bring back the Ascended Sage, and go for Tornado, and then Utopic Future into Utopic Draco Future.  If you discard a ZS when getting to the 3 Onomat cards, by means of Onomatopaira, you wait to use dragonar, then use entrust to summon the discarded ZS, and  you make Future Draco. Then summon Lancelot off of Dragonar.  Thank you for going through the guide and dedicating a good 2-3 hours into reading, and good luck, have fun!  (Last side note, I swear. This deck is completely legal in Master Duel, so consider using this if you're willing to spend a few hundred more!)

deck_excerpt: A deck meant to OTK with big boss monsters and look pretty while doing so.
deck_description: Oh, Tiger is at 3 in Master Duel? Don't mind if I do... The strategy is simple-beat over your opponent by dancing their butts off (Leo Dancer+a link boss monster or another copy of itself. Preferably with Chick banished for no battle phase shenanigans.) Core Ratios: Main Deck 3) Tiger because soft One Per Turn clauses are easily subverted by bouncing. Also a Daruma Doll target for backrow popping/revivial Marten because you can bounce Tiger and get more fusion/link material through its revival(or go into Tiger King) Kaldeo Chick because 1)dumping for cost means negates don't affect the dumping, 2)you can cheat our your fusions with the name change, 3)battle protection means no 3500 damage to you via Magic Cylinder, and 4)Polymerization recycling. Also level 4 for Tiger King. Lunalight Fusion, despite being a Hard Once Per Turn, means you can get Leo Dancer out with two Lunalight Monsters in hand and an Extra Deck on the opp's field. Also searchable by Marten. Luna Light Perfume (which, do note, is NOT searchable by Marten because of that extra space in "Luna Light") is archetypal Revival and Deck searching, not Once Per Turn. Need I say more? 2) White Rabbit is nice revival and backrow bouncing, but having the revival on normal summon is rough due to Chick usually being a better call. Emerald Bird is nice recovery, helps un-brick hands and get other Lunalights into grave and yet another Tiger King material...but Chick is still a better normal summon, and the discard can be a bit awkward. Black Sheep...honestly could be at 3, since it pays for itself through both of its effects, but I find that it being in your opening hand with no other lunalights in hand can be rough. Allure of Darkness because you run a lot of Darks, but you do have the occasional Light monster. I can see this at 3 if you can take the risk. 1) Tenki honestly could also be at 3 since it is an amazing searcher, but usually 1 does the job enough for me. More room for handtraps. Foolish Burial Goods could also be at three since it gets Perfume and Serenade Dance into grave, but as one who doesn't run Pots, hand space can be tight. Purple Butterfly is nice attack boosting and gets Lunalights out of  your hand, but I would rather see it more in grave than in hand. Blue Cat because you only need one for the atk boost and sadly Mystic Tomato strats in this day and age aren't nearly as viable with all the negates and banishing. Crimson Fox is nice targeting protection and atk dropping which is good for early setup or baiting, but your Big Boss Fusions all have some protection and you have other ways of boosting attack. Polymerization/Fusion Substitute since you can recover both via Chick...but you also have Lunalight Fusion. Serenade Dance is something you want to see in grave far more than in hand for the revival effect, but at least is a target for Martin in a pinch and an extra card for White Rabbit bouncing (remember, Lunalight cards, not just Monsters). Revolt because it is a nice way to recover your banished monsters...but you probably have your other Tri-Brigade links in the grave barring Shuraig, so having more than one can be dead draws.   Extra Deck 2) All fusions but Cat Dancer-Two Leo Dancers are more than enough to OTK, Two Saber Dancers to have one on field and one for the attack boost, Two Panther Dancers in case they banish your first from the grave. 1) Cat Dancer mostly because you'll be dumping Panther Dancer through Chick instead. Is a nice first turn option if you can't get to Leo Dancer, though. Tri-Brigade links are pretty much to get a banish off the field or to link climb into your other archetypal boss monsters. Daruma Doll is nice backrow removal and helps link climb.   Optional Staples Main Deck Maxx C gives you a free turn to OTK or helps unbrick a hand. Called by The Grave makes sure no Ashes ruin your Perfume searches. Forbidden Droplet since it gets things into grave as well as negates your opp's boss monster Twin Twisters and Harpies' Feather Duster because, since this is Best of 1, backrow removal is a good bit more important if you don't want Eldlich/Sky Striker to ruin your day. Raigeki/Lightning Storm because nothing is more funny than blowing up a field that your opponent played Solitaire to get. Monster Reborn because being a lesser Luna Light Perfume is still pretty nice. Extra Deck Accesscode OTK's with a Link 3 material and Leo Dancer, though I can see Borrelsword being here as well. Masquerena gives your Link-4 Boss monsters some protection Avramax is more of a first turn option, since it is an annoyance to get off the field with Masquerena protection and can't be beaten over unless they force a negate.   This is probably not the most optimized build, so modify this at your leisure, but I feel this is a decent skeleton for the Lunalight deck in Master Duel. Have fun dancing your way to OTKs!

  • The deck must tell something about you and/or personality;
  • Explain the strategy of your deck;
  • Your deck doesnt need to be top tier or anything, so lets just forget about the meta this time;
  • Tips for improoving are welcome however;
  • State in the deck master area what is your ace card;
  • Preferentially, dont explain the non-strategical reasons why you choose the cards in your deck, lets the deck tell for itself;
  • Lets be respectiful, its always good.

deck_excerpt: Smash your opponent by being annoying
deck_description: I main lava golem because it counters most decks, the only deck it doesn't really counter is mirror match or Sky strikers. Also, Lava Golem + Gozen Match/Rivalry of Warlords, is pretty strong and annoying locking your opponent to Fire or Fiend. Against Swordsoul and PK its strong.   Rivalry won't be as strong next meta because PK and Swordsoul will dominate as DIS (Dogmatika, Invoker, Shadoll) won't be as played as much with the recent small nerf. But with the new brave Engine it will actually mess up a lot of decks that use Brave engine, due to the token being a fairy, as a lot of rouge decks that use brave engine will start to pop up and may become meta like ABC's.    Side deck is probably weird, but this is for the next Meta.  Dark bribe in General is a trash card and you're wondering why not just run the 3rd judgment? After play testing you are using a shit ton of life points from solemn judgement, solemn strike, and the 3 skill drains. you will always be on the edge of life points, and I've had dead cards like strike and skill drain because I've used so much life points especially solemn judgment due to force negate like lightning storm and twin twisters of course I could always use Eldlich to just dump dead cards. In a floodgate/stun deck, it's not a bad card letting your opponent draw one card while skill drained, gozen matched, etc, it isn't going to do much. Letting your opponent Draw one card unless they draw another spell/trap removal it's not a bad card. If I had 5 back row and had some floodgate cards like summon limit or solemn strike, they lightning storm me I would rather dark bribe than solemn judgment. Also, you won't get psy-gamma and can stop cosmic cyclone. Why Summon limit? A strong going first turn card, shuts down every combo decks. but it's just my personal preference.  Reason why I run 3 twin twisters instead of 3 lightning storm is because after play testing a lot of people have been siding royal degrees. The issue with lighting storm is when u flip a floodgate card like gozen match you can't activate lightning storm of course u have ways like using Eldlich but twin twisters just way more reliable removing royal degree and back row because it's a quick spell. Artifact lancea > Iron wall, Lancea is strong against evenly match and cosmic cyclone.  The imperial iron wall is extremely strong against in mirror match or decks that banishes a lot more than you but use it wisely as it hurts you as well, but you have the power to pop your own iron wall. You're going 2nd cards lava, golem, super poly, and Lancea.   your super poly targets and when to side super poly in. 1.Eldlich the Mad Golden Lord (Eldlich" monster + 1 Level 5 or higher Zombie monster) Good for Mirror match or for some reason zombie decks. 2. Predaplant Triphyoverutum (3 DARK monsters on the field) This game can win you games it has a really good effect and u can target 3 dark monsters very powerful against Phantom knights  3. Starving Venom Fusion Dragon (2 DARK monsters on the field, except Tokens) Good against Phantom Knights or combine it with Verte and Dragoon 4. Mudragon of the Swamp (2 monsters with the same Attribute but different Types) Another good backup fusion. 5. Prank-Kids Weather Washer - (2 "Prank-Kids" monsters) Prank kids. Becoming meta this format.

deck_excerpt: Cyber Dragon pure deck build with Cyberdark side deck for a hybrid Cyber Dragon/Cyberdark deck.
deck_description:
Cyber Dragons are known for being OTK decks with their extra deck monsters, Cyber End Dragon being the most iconic. Though OTKs are what most Cyber Dragon decks are known for the purpose of this Cyber Dragon deck build deck is to be a control beatdown deck using Cybernetic Overflow to help control, Cyber Dragon Infinity to help stun, and Cyberload Fusion to help push for OTK. There are various ways to go into Cyber Dragon Nova and Cyber Dragon Infinity YET timing their summons is crucial. Several times going into Cyber Dragon Nova and Cyber Dragon Infinity is not necessary.

 

This deck build runs 3 copies of Cybernetic Overflow to help control and 2 copies of Cyberload Fusion to take full advantage of Cybernetic Overflow's banishing costs (Keep in mind that if Cybernetic Overflow is destroyed while on field it becomes an extender by helping add 1 "Cyber" Spell/Trap from deck to hand). Machine Duplication is a VERY powerful card and is ran at 2, 3 can become bricks. (Helps go into Cyber Dragon Nova which can then go into Cyber Dragon Infinity very quickly). Cyber Repair Plant is ran at 3 to further help deck search especially when needing to search for Jizukiru, the Star Destroying Kaiju. (Can easily be ran at 2 or 1 depending on preference). Foolish Burial is primarily used to trigger Cyber Dragon Herz (Can also be used to set up a Cyber Dragon in GY if Cyber Dragon Nachster is in hand for Cyber Dragon Nachster to be normal or special summoned to then target Cyber Dragon in GY and special summon it OR to have more Cyber Dragon variety in GY for Cybernetic Overflow's banishing costs). One for One is primarily used to help set up a board for Machine Duplication though One for One can be used in many different ways depending on resources on field, hand and grave (Can be used to send Cyber Dragon Herz from hand to GY to trigger Herz effect, Can be used to special summon Herz to trigger Herz special summon effect, Can be used to special summon Cyber Dragon Nachster to trigger Cyber Dragon Nachster's effect, Can be used to help set the board for a Cyber Dragon Drei normal summon effect, Can be used to have variance for Cybernetic Overflow). Running 2 Cyber Dragon Sieger, 2 Chimeratech Fortress Dragon and 2 Chimeratech Megafleet Dragon makes this build a bit more competitive and can easily be done by taking out the 3 Cyberdark fusion monsters.

 

 

 

Key Takeaways:

 

Cyber Dragon Core - Literally the core of this deck. Normal summon to add 1 "Cyber" Spell/trap from deck to hand. Can literally search all "Cyber" Spell/Trap cards including Cyberdark spells and traps. Cyber Dragon Core can be targeted by Machine Duplication.

 

Cyber Emergency - Literally the extender of this deck. Adds 1 "Cyber Dragon" monster from deck to hand or 1 Light machine monster that cannot be normal summoned/Set (Cyber Eltanin)

 

Cyber Dragon Herz - When Special summoned its level becomes 5. When sent to graveyard it allows to to add 1 "Cyber Dragon" from Deck or GY to hand. (Keep in mind all monsters in this deck build are considered "Cyber Dragon" when on field or graveyard, allowing Cyber Dragon Herz to add any Cyber Dragon monsters from graveyard back to hand). Cyber Dragon Herz can be targeted by Machine Duplication.

 

Cyber Dragon Nachster - When normal or special summoned you can target 1 machine monster with 2100 ATK or DEF in your GY, special summon it. (Ideal combo is to special summon Cyber Dragon Nachster from hand by sending an original Cyber Dragon from hand to GY then targeting that sent Cyber Dragon in GY and special summoning it. Targets that Cyber Dragon Nachster can special summon from graveyard are Cyber Dragon, Cyber Dragon Nova,Cyber Dragon Infinity, Cyberdark Chimera. Cyber Twin Dragon, and Chimeratech Rampage Dragon) Cyber Dragon Nachster can be targeted by Machine Duplication.

 

Cyber Dragon Drei - When normal summoned you can make all "Cyber Dragon" you currently control become level 5. (Ideal combo for Cyber Dragon Drei is activating Cyber Dragon Nachster effect in hand to special summon Cyber Dragon Nachster then following up with normal summoning Cyber Dragon Drei to convert all Cyber Dragon monsters on field to LVL 5 then to go into Cyber Dragon Nova and Cyber Dragon Infinity). Another way to make Cyber Dragon Nova is by having Cyber Dragon Vier in hand when normal summoning Cyber Dragon Drei. (When normal summoned Cyber Dragon Drei's effect can be activated AND Cyber Dragon Vier's special summon effect can be chained to Cyber Dragon Drei's effect to make both Cyber Dragon Drei and Cyber Dragon Vier level 5).

 

Cyber Dragon Vier - Can be Special summoned from hand in DEF position if you normal or special summon "Cyber Dragon". Gives each "Cyber Dragon: you control a 500 ATK and DEF boost. (This is a special summon after summoning any Cyber Dragon monster. Helps have resources for going into Cyber Dragon Sieger AND can be chained to Cyber Dragon Drei's normal summon effect to help make resources for Cyber Dragon Nova).

 

Cyber Eltanin - helps clear the board; when summoned, sends all monsters on the field to the GY. Can be searched with Cyber Emergency and Cyber Repair Plant. Cyber Eltanin's special summon requirements also helps push all Cyber Dragon variants from fiedl and GY to the banish pile setting up resources for a Cyberload Fusion OTK. 

 

Jizukiru, Kaiju - helps get rid of an opponent's OMNI negate and can be contact fused with any "Cyber Dragon" on the field to make Chimeratech Fortress Dragon. Can also be used to make Chimeratech Megafleet Dragon if opponent has a monster in an extra monster zone. Can only be searched with Cyber Repair Plant.

 

 

 

 

Cyberdark Side Deck 

 

Cyberdark cards can easily be swapped in by cutting down on "3 ofs" and "2 ofs".

 

When swapping in Cyberdark cards please keep in mind that this dilutes the Cyber Dragon 

deck build consistency. Having familiarity with how how Cyber Dragon and Cyberdark work individually vastly helps. When familiarized and when playing a hybrid deck more than not Cyber Dragon and Cyberdark build on top of another. Both Cyber Dragon Core and Cybernetic Overflow strongly support both archetypes due to how both are capable of searching any Cyber spell/trap. 

 

 

Ideally these are the cards that are removed from the main deck and the whole side deck is then swapped in to make a Cyber Dragon/Cyberdark deck:

 

Cyber Dragon Herz (-1)

 

Cyber Drago Nachster (-1)

 

Cyber Dragon Drei (-1)

 

Cyber Dragon Vier (-1)

 

Jizukiru, the Star Destroying Kaiju (-1)

 

Cyber Eltanin (-1) 

 

Cyber Emergency (-1)

 

Cyber Repair Plant (-1)

 

Cyber Revsystem (-1)

 

Cyberload Fusion (-1)

 

Machine Duplication (-1)

 

Red Reboot (-1)

deck_excerpt: Competitive in Platinum
deck_description:
I got to Platinum with an incomplete and much less potent version of this deck. After hitting platinum I swapped to Sky Striker so not sure how it fairs beyond that. It's a modification of my 2020 OCG deck with minor differences, read it up to understand its combos there. Some key differences:
  • Dragoon is banned, so verte is usually used to fuse Magicians' Souls and Magician Rod together to get Dark Magician/Dark Magician girl on the field (depending which one you already have in GY, go for the other) through fusion deployment, instead of Red Eyes Fusion.
  • Current environment is thriving with decks like Drytron so Nibiru is really great for that, though if you run into too much Eldritch you may take 1 out, or both.
  • Palladium Oracle Mana isn't in so it kind of hurts a bit. Otherwise, if you can get number 42 out, you could summon Ip, vertes, and union train equip mana, and summon Mekkknight Crusadia next turn, dumping all 4 Soul Servant cards in the GY for insane draw. Moreover Mana just helps giving you a sticky board and some protection which is always nice, especially since you should not rely on eterneral soul too much.
  • Currently Illusion of Chaos is also not available yet, but highly recommend going all three, really helps with bricking problem.

deck_excerpt: Competitive Spirit Charmer - Easy to obtain/cheap - Strategies are straightforward  - Spellcaster/Dragon type Deck Difficulties: ⅗ combo type Cha
deck_description: Yu-Gi-Oh! Duel Master: Charmers Deck The “Charmer”, or known as the “Spirit Charmer” is a standalone archetype of Spellcaster monster themed on controlling monsters with the same Attribute as them which is unfortunately not playable in any way without an exceptional support from another card. Surprisingly the new Archetype called “Magistus” came out soon after the “Spirit Charmer” was released in 2021. The “Magistus” archetype had a perfect synergy for the “Charmers” especially since they only rely on base from Attribute and Types. This deck is strong enough to be used in high Tier level on Master Duel or Tournaments(hopefully).... This build is very easy to obtain/play it and can be used for any newcomer duelist because most of the cards are actually straightforward for the combos which I already listed the key cards for anyone interested to play Charmer Deck. Start with only using 3 simple Key Cards which is the only best I ever come out with for the Full Charmer's combos. Just following the recommendation cards that are listed below. ___________________________________________ [Key Cards]: 3 Main Engine - Spirit Charmers - Performage Damage Juggler - Zoroa, the Magistus of Flame [Recommend] to Search/Use - Lyna the Light Charmer (Hand) & Awakening of the Possessed (Spell/Trap Zone) - Performage Trick Clown (Hand) - Artemis, the Magistus Moon Maiden (Spell/Trap Zone) = Crowley, the Magistus of Grimoires (Hand) ___________________________________________ Once you finally set up your cards. You will proceed with the next step by activating “Crowley, the Magistus of Grimoires” effect to send out “Lyna, the Light Charmer” from your hand to the GY. Then use "Crowley, the Magistus of Grimoires" effect to become Earth Attribute that allowed you to Summon “Awakening of the Possessed - Nefariouser Archfiend'' card from either hand or Deck by sending both “Crowley, the Magistus of Grimoires” and “Performage Trick Clown” from the field to the GY, which make them to trigger of their effects by Chain Link 2 and bringing it back “Lyna, the Light Charmer” from the GY to the field along with “Performage Trick Clown” by it own effect. Now you have finally had a chance to Summon “Familiar-Possessed Lyna” from either hand or Deck by its own effect. After that use “Familiar-Possessed Lyna” effect to search out “Dogmatika Ecclesia, the Virtuous” from your Deck then add it to your hand which is the only best Spellcaster monster with 1500 DEF/Level 4/Light Attribute monster that can be able to search out by "Familiar-Possessed - Dharc" effect when it Summoned by it own effect. Reminder: Do not activate "Dogmatika Ecclesia, the Virtuous" effect during your turn when it Summoned to your field, it will disable you for summoning from the Exta Deck unless if you have too. (This is an Optional) ___________________________________________ Tips: You might not actually get them from the opening hand with exactly cards. So I prefer you to try something else with different cards in your hand if one of the Key Cards are missing. You should better rely on your additional cards in your hand that might help you to set up your cards. Keep it in your mind that "Spirit Charmers" is just an additional card to use Familiar-Possessed - Lyna's Effect to search out "Dogmatika Ecclesia, the Virtuous" from your deck to the hand. ___________________________________________ [Additional] for more Consistency You can use "Summoner Monk" as additional for "Zoroa, the Magistus of Flame" or any Level 4 monster from your Deck like "Rilliona, the Magistus of Verre" or any Performage monster depending what card you need. Requirement: 1 any Spell card, except "Spirit Charmers" card, if not, you can use it as well if you have too. I include “Summoner Monk” from my Deck Profile since It actually works very well for any Level 4 monster. ___________________________________________ The End Board got changed frequently due to lack of cards since I actually used Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon lately in the actual game which is not my original plan for this deck. So I came up with the new play style by giving you more options to play either "Number 106: Giant Hand" or summon any link 2 like "Predaplant Verte Anaconda" depending on any situation if you have more additional cards on your play to expand it. I want to try something new in Master Duel with different cards that I have so it got changed especially from the Extra Deck. You can still use I:P Masquerena as usual to link summon “Selene, Queen of the Master Magicians” or "Knightmare Unicorn" during your opponent's turn. There's a ton of cards that can be used for the Charmer deck strategies with different combination cards as we play them. You can still change it and/or make them stronger as you like. Just be more creative and make it simple as long as you're having fun...

deck_description: thanks to El-Exordio's video for most of the main core of the main deck, but i'm pretty sure i changed about 40% of the deck, basically making it more my deck with just using the must-have core ratios used from exordio's decklist. some of the changes i did were: budget/collection: took out droplets, the F0 engine, AA-ZEUS, and the earths (gallant and gigantes) due to not having them for price reasons or just not having them in my collection personal: i added a second DoN! for the reason of not wanting to brick on it, it really mentally hurts a lot to see the only copy of it in a hand where the only play you can really do is to summon double. And i swapped an astraltopia for a second astral kuriboh cause in playtesting if you draw too much astraltopia you're kinda dead in the water. aand i also swapped tornado for lightning blade. banlist: added feather duster to the main deck due to skill drain being unlimited, although i took out xyz tactics for it buut basically the card isn't really needed and more overkill than nessesary, plus i don't really want to be drawing into any of my searchables with it either. and for the extra deck i basically remade it, due to opening a bunch of space from F0 and the searcher xyz's going away, i added a second U-Double and utopia, and some more dragonar targets with 71, 84, 41, and 4(kragen). i also took out tornado dragon due to skill drain.   i would replace the effect veilers here for forbidden chalice, but i currently don't have any forbidden chalices

deck_excerpt: Madolche play style
deck_description: The main part of madolche is consistency. The deck is capable to break board going second. It can also build a decent board going first. However, the main issue with madolche is consistency. Therefore, pot of prosperity is important. If pot of prosperity is too expensive, pot of extravagance can replace however it is way less good since madolche do not need the extra card. They need the key card. The second card is small world. It allows to search mageline, angelly or petite through hand traps which are all key starters of the combo. ex of small world: ash blossom -> hootcake -> and lvl4 madolche, or ghost bell -> veiler -> mageline  Having different hand trap for small world is also in synergy with crossout.  depending on the handtrap that you have there are multiple different ways to search the card through small world. If both previously mentioned cards are too expensive, you can choose to play a more going second version which drops all hand trap, pot, and small world (I admit that they are expensive) and adds cards which break boards such as dark ruler, harpie, kaiju, nibiru, and raigeki (back at 3 with the jan 2022 banlist).  In this deck, there is no side deck because it really depends on the format.  I do suggest cards like dark ruler, dimension shifter, lancea, droll. Regardless of what you choose, I suggest choosing cards that either has a board wipe or influence the entire board effect such as dark ruler or card that apply a rule such as droll, lancea which denie your opponent from one type of effect.  If cards like lightning storm aren't accessible and you need back role removal. Hey Tsunade is a decent choice. Since you do not need multiple turns as madolche player. 1 Turn is often enough.  Personally, the key card that wins me most of my duels is madolche teacher glassoufle. The shuffle-back effect from both gy is a really annoying effect for current format decks. The hard part is to know when to activate it. You have to do it 1 step before your opponent's foolish-like effect. Not 2 steps just 1 in order to trigger glassoufle's effect in the next chainlink.     Reglardless, Madolche is a deck that have a lot of potential. It is not hard to learn the combo and fun deck.

deck_excerpt: A very fun going second blind OTK Deck. We basically spin all of our opponent cards to their deck and swing with exactly 8000 for game.
deck_description:
Your goal with this deck is to (preferably) go second and utilize the Mekk-Knights to generate advantage with columns utilizing the cards from your opponent, especially with Purple Nightfall and Indigo Eclipse, to summon Rainbow Neos through Verte Anaconda. Then, you will use Rainbow Neos effect to spin all of your opponent monsters or backrow using Verte as fodder or the spells/trap you used to create columns in the first place. Also, since we're playing the Invoked Engine, we also want to setup Invoked Mechaba as soon as possible, since his 2500 ATK + 4500 ATK from Rainbow Neos + using Aleister effect from the hand to boost one of the 2 fusion by 1000 ATK = exactly 8000 LP for the OTK. Some additional info:
  • Why play Sangan? - We're playing Sangan since the deck would lack a good Normal Summon other than Aleister. We can link him off with Almiraj and get to search for any handtrap in the deck or Orange Sunset, which if we have a column setup with Almiraj, we can Special Summon him and link for Verte and so forth.
PS: Lightning Storm is kinda of a double-edge sword and very situational in this deck because it does its job too well. You wanna consider that the cards you're destroying clean-up the columns for your Mekk-Knights, so use it at your own discretion.

deck_excerpt: A deck I exclusively used to reach Platinum Tier 1 on Master Duel. The Arrival Cyberse having effect immunity gives it unique advantages over certain
deck_description:
-Strategy The main advantage this deck has are the 1-card combos. This gives you a lot of room for the rest of your hand to be dedicated for either countering the opponent's boards or protecting your own plays. When going first, the goal is to combo into The Arrival Cyberse + Cyberse Quantum Dragon. Most decks can't deal with The Arrival, so as long as you can protect it from getting beaten over you should have control of the game. When going second, you combo into the 2300 attack Extra Deck @Ignisters and Accesscode Talker to boardwipe the opponent and go for an OTK. -Decklist
  1. Achichi/Pikari/Cynet Mining/AI Meet You: These are all essentially your 1-card combo starters. In mid to late game, Pikari gains greater value due to it's ability to search for the in-themed Monster Reborn cards. Do note that AI Meet You is not usually used as a combo starter, so if you use it that way it will produce the weakest board (The Arrival Cyberse without Cyberse Quantum Dragon.)
  2. Ignister AILand/Doyon/Buruburu/Danmari: These are all combo pieces that you get out from the deck to continue your combo. Ignister AILand is used to enable your special summons. Doyon adds @Ignister monsters and spells back to your hand. Buruburu is the Tuner of the deck which can be searched by Cyberse Wicckid. Danmari can be sent from the deck to the grave via Buruburu which allows it to be used as a one time Omni-Negate as long as The Arrival Cyberse on board.
  3. FAIghting Spirit/AIdle Reborn/Monster Reborn: These are all basically Monster Reborn which allows you to recover your plays in case you get interrupted. If you have at least 2 of these, you can recover from Nibiru depending on where in the combo it is activated. FAIghting Spirit has an interesting interaction with Achichi's graveyard effect which results in The Arrival Cyberse from being unable to be destroyed by battle.
  4. Maxx C/Nibiru/Ash Blossom/Ghost Belle/Infinite Impermanence: Due to how compact the combos are, you can afford to play a large variety of hand traps. Maxx C is the only I really consider a must have since it can unbrick your hand or let you draw into Forbidden Droplet or your other handtraps. The rest is up to preference. I only play 1 Ash Blossom and 1 Impermanence for Crossout Designator. Ghost Belle has some interesting application against meta decks like Eldlich and Tri-Brigade, but it is replaceable for something else if you prefer.
  5. Called by the Grave/Crossout Designator: The deck is vulnerable to handtraps so these cards are necessary for protecting your combos.
  6. Forbidden Droplet: Useful whether you are going first or second. When going second, this is your main board breaking card outside of Nibiru. When going first, the attacking reducing effect helps protect The Arrival Cyberse from getting beaten over.
-Extra Deck Combo Routes
  1. Dark Infant -> Cyberse Wicckid -> Splash Mage -> Dark Templar (Preferably in the right EMZ) -> Route A or B
A) Summon your second Dark Infant under Dark Templar in the middle column and then combo into Cyberse Quantum Dragon and then The Arrival Cyberse right after. B) Summon your second Dark Infant under Dark Templar in the middle column and then combo into Wind Pegasus, Light Dragon, and Accesscode Talker for boardwiping and OTK. 2. Accesscode Talker Double Attack OTK If you can summon Splash Mage + another Cyberse monster, then you can use Splash Mage's effect to revive a monster from the graveyard. From there, you can link the revived monster and your other Cyberse monster on the field for Update Jammer. Link Update Jammer and Splash Mage for Accesscode Talker. Doing this will enable Accesscode Talker to attack twice for an OTK. This is the most resource efficient OTK, but should only be done as a last resort if combo 2B fails or cannot be done. -Notes
  1. Space Insulator is used as generic Cyberse Link in order to get rid of things like Nibiru, Nibiru Tokens, and Lost World Tokens off of your field. This is because @Ignister AILand's effect cannot activate as long such cards are in your Main Monster Zone.  
  2. Update Jammer's board effect doesn't reduce The Arrival's attack to 0, so you can use these two together to beat over an unusually high attack power monster. However, this is a really rare scenario.
